title: spoon bread
directions: Pour water over corn meal.
Add butter and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Add milk, egg yolks and baking powder, then fold in the stiffly beaten whites of 3 eggs.
Pour into a greased Pyrex baking dish and bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crockpot candy
directions: In a large round crockpot, layer ingredients as listed.
Do not mix or stir.
Cook on low heat for two hours.
Do not lift lid.
After two hours, stir well; drop by teaspoonful on to waxed paper.
Let cool until firm before removing.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Mix together Rice Krispies, syrup (any kind) and peanut butter.
Spread into a casserole dish or a pie pan.
Add ice cream on top of mixture.
Top with bananas, chocolate syrup and whatever you desire.
(You need to eat this soon after you fix it, because Rice Krispies get a little tough.)
Easy and delicious.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift flour, add baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift again. Beat eggs and add to milk.
Combine liquid with dry ingredients, fold in nuts.
Let stand in loaf pan for 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts in bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour over coconut and nuts. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out.
The bottom makes the icing.
Mix first 3 ingredients and spread over cake.

title: game meat steaks
directions: Slice meat thin into strips; brown slightly.
Add onion, mushrooms, tomatoes, gravy package and water.
Stir; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: mexican quiche
directions: On floured pastry sheet roll pastry to 12-inch circle; place in pie pan.
Fold under extra pastry; flute edges.
Line unpricked pastry with 2 layers heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes more or until nearly done.
Keep warm.

title: sour orange pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt together.
Add boiling water, juice and grated rind.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shells and chill.

title: super salad
directions: Combine undrained fruit in a bowl.
Add marshmallows, stir in pudding mix; add whipped topping and mix.
Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat oil until hot in an iron skillet.
Add rice and stir constantly until it is nice and brown.
Remove from heat and drain off all the oil.
Add spices and stir briefly.
Add onion, tomatoes, pepper and water.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Cover pot, lower heat and allow to simmer.
Do not stir.
Cook until it has absorbed all the liquid, being careful not to allow it to burn.
Serves 4.

title: "seven day" slaw(from hudson's restaurant in hilton head, south carolina)
directions: Slice cabbage and onion thinly or shred them.
Toss with 1/3 cup sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage.
Let set and, in 5 minutes, mix. Chill in refrigerator and serve on leaves of romaine.
Serves 4.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray. Saute garlic and onion until soft. Add remaining ingredients, and bring to a boil. Using a potato masher, mash squash and potato until soup is very thick. Add more liquid as desired and simmer for 20 minutes. If desired, add coarsely chopped turkey kielbasa sausage while simmering. Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: monkey's delight sandwich spread(kid's sandwiches; prep time: 5 minutes)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the peanut butter, cream cheese and milk. Stir until well mixed. Stir in pineapple, carrot and banana. Makes 2 sandwiches. Your choice of bread. Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up chicken.
Put in pan with water, onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Boil until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from pan. Cool. Save chicken stock.
Debone chicken and add to chicken stock.
Bring to a boil.
Drop biscuits into chicken broth.
Cook until biscuits are tender.
Serves 4.

title: praline cookies
directions: Melt butter and blend in sugar.
Add eggs, nuts, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Prepare a well greased heavy cookie sheet. Drop one-half teaspoon of batter for each cookie, placing them five inches apart.
Bake about 10 minutes in a moderate oven.
Then loosen edges of each cookie with a wide spatula and lift onto a wire cake rack to cool and crisp.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and flour, blending well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour and cook until blended.
Heat milk; blend in flour and butter mixture and cook until thick.
Add cheese; mix with peas and mushrooms.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake 25 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat. Saute celery and onion until tender.
Add potatoes and broth. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 12 minutes). Sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Slice the cucumbers, onions, celery and green peppers in a large bowl. Add the pimentos.
Combine the salt, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Cook until clear; cool.
Pour over cucumbers. Chill and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat.
Beat eggs well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Sprinkle pecans in.

title: mahogany chiffon cake(family favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place 2 packets of chocolate into small bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until blended.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Make a well.
Add oil, egg yolks, vanilla and chocolate mixture in this order.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Add cream of tartar to the egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Gently fold egg whites into other mixture and continue to gently blend egg whites into the mixture.
Slowly pour entire mixture into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.
Bake at 350° for an additional 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool inverted for several hours.
Make buttercream frosting and frost before serving. This is a large cake and goes far.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Serve with any fruit.

title: kim's chicken salad(serves 6)
directions: Combine chicken, celery and lemon juice and chill well. Combine mayonnaise, sour cream and salad dressing mix (use dressing sparingly or to taste); cover and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add green grapes and mandarin oranges before serving.
If salad is too dry, add juice from oranges.
Serve on lettuce bed with 1 cantaloupe sprinkled with sugared almonds.

title: lucky if you get a piece(strawberry dessert)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into pan; bake at 350° until browned.

title: hot and spicy nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt the butter in a medium size saucepan over low heat.
Add the remaining ingredients except the nuts and coarse salt.
Simmer over low heat for several minutes to combine flavors.
Add the nuts and stir until evenly coated. Spread on baking sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes, shaking the pan occasionally.
Toss the nuts with the coarse salt and let cool. Store in an airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: hamburger veggie delight
directions: Boil cut up cabbage and onions in small amount of water.
Boil until soft, adding tomatoes while cooking.
Mix ground beef and rice into meatballs.
Place in cooking pot.
Cook on medium heat until meatballs are done, then simmer.

title: chili corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chilies .
Pour half of batter in iron skillet.
Cover with half of the cheese and chili peppers.
Cover with rest of the batter and top with rest of cheese and peppers.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing from skillet.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Toss with chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate before serving. Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick and easy coffee cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix 1/2 melted oleo with 1/2 cup sugar.
Then add egg, milk, flour and baking powder.
Pour batter into buttered pan (8 x 8-inch).
Pour oleo over and sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon over batter.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: asparagus and ham topper
directions: Place hot potatoes split on a microwave safe plate. Fluff potatoes with a fork and top with ham. Stir soup until very smooth. Spoon soup over potatoes. Top with cheese and microwave on high about 4 minutes or until hot.

title: freeze ahead meat sauce
directions: Break up ground beef in large pot. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until some fat has collected. Add onion, garlic and salt. Cook until onion and garlic are tender. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1 hour until sauce is thickened. Let cool and if too much fat has accumulated, skim off. Pack in pint or quart freezer containers and freeze. Makes 3 quarts.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream the margarine
and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Sift dry ingredients together.
Alternate dry ingredients with Ricotta and vanilla in the margarine and sugar. Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. After cooled, use powdered sugar icing to ice and you can add sprinkles.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine and put most on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften 1/2 gallon ice cream (any flavor) and spread on top of the crust.
Put remaining mixture on top and freeze.

title: zippy cheese ball
directions: Cut olives and smoked beef into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Best if made the day before you plan to eat it.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, broccoli, onion, 6 tablespoons butter and muffin mix; beat well. Pour remaining butter into a 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Pour batter into skillet and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pita breakfast
directions: Stuff Pita bread with pre-warmed ham and fried eggs (break yolks) cooked in Mazola corn oil.
Wrap in tinfoil to keep warm and moist.

title: blueberry or peach crunch
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour pineapple in pan.
Spread fruit over pineapple.
Pour 3/4 cup sugar over fruit.
Sprinkle box of cake mix over sugar.
Melt oleo and pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over oleo.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 38 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cut through cake and let juice rise up.
Cook 15 minutes more.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Put ingredients into a 4 or 5-quart crock-pot in the order listed. Cover and cook for 3 hours on low. DO NOT REMOVE LID!! Turn off and cool slightly. Mix thoroughly and drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let cool. (Makes approximately 170 pieces.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Layer crumbled Ritz crackers and butter on bottom.
Put chicken, soup, broth and sour cream on top of crackers and butter.
Then put another layer of crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine carrots, onions and green pepper in large bowl.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables in bowl. Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Drain, reserving marinade.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl, if desired.
Return any leftover vegetables to marinade; keep refrigerated.
Yields 5 cups.
Will keep several weeks.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream first 3 ingredients; add next 2. Press into spring-form pan, on bottom and up sides.
Refrigerate.

title: milkshake
directions: Add all ingredients except ice cubes.
Blend until frothy.
Add ice cubes 1 at a time and blend well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients together in a large pan.
Form into a loaf.
If desired, place 2 strips bacon on top and pour over all an 8 ounce can of tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: basic chiffon cake
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Sift the first 4 ingredients together into a mixing bowl.
Make a well and add the oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat until smooth with a spoon (with electric beater, use medium speed for 1 minute).
Add cream of tartar to egg whites in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with rotary beater until the whites form very stiff peaks.
With an electric beater, use high speed 3 to 5 minutes.
It is important not to underbeat. Pour the egg yolk mixture gradually over the beaten egg whites, folding with a rubber scraper until just blended.
Do not stir. Pour into a 9 x 3 1/2-inch tube pan or an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan or a 10 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in square pan or 50 to 55 minutes in loaf
or tube pan.
Turn the pan upside down, free of table, until cold.
When cake is completely cold, loosen around the sides with a spatula.
Turn the pan over and hit the edge sharply on the table to loosen.
Cake will drop out.

title: creamy casserole
directions: Layer choice size casserole dish with potatoes. Then layer with sliced onions; not too many. Then layer with cabbage; I like a lot. Add soup according to the size casserole dish you are using. Add a little water. Now put cooked hamburger on top. Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. May take longer if you are using a large dish. You may cover the dish if hamburger starts to burn.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients while hot, then let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: imitation crab cakes
directions: Add eggs to zucchini, then everything else.
Mix and make patties. Fry.

title: millie's broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Steam a bunch of broccoli and chop in small pieces.
Boil chicken and cool, then chop into small bite sizes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and mix remaining ingredients.
Turn out dough to floured board and knead 50 times. Shape into rolls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix the cookie crumbs with the sugar in a bowl. Stir in the butter. Press onto the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Spoon half the ice cream into the crust. Drizzle with half the chocolate syrup; swirl with a knife. Spoon the remaining ice cream carefully over the top. Drizzle with remaining syrup.

title: roast beef for 100
directions: Use the largest roasting pans available.
Spear roasts with meat fork multiple times.
Put 1 tablespoon of flour into 3 to 4 large Reynolds oven cooking bags and shake (this keeps bag from bursting in oven).
Place roasts in cooking bags; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour dressing over roasts and tie bags with plastic ties provided with bags.
Refrigerate overnight to marinate meat.
Don't poke holes in bags per the instructions until ready to put roasts in the oven.
Turn meat over at least once or twice during marinating time to get dressing on all sides. Cook in ovens (only at Epworth United Methodist Church) at 325° for 4 to
4 1/2 hours to insure the meat is tender and juicy. Slice and serve for Wednesday night dinner.
This is the only place and time that I have been able to get this recipe to turn out right.

title: italian turkey stuffing(9 pound turkey)
directions: Place rice in a large bowl.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread.
Soak bread in lukewarm water until soft.
Squeeze a little water out and add to bowl.
Mix well.
Works best if allowed to set overnight 1 or 2 days before stuffing.
Add salt to taste.
Stuff just before baking.

title: aunt emma's corny dogs
directions: Heat wieners in hot water; thoroughly drain.
Have ready deep fat for frying.
Combine all ingredients.
Dip hot wieners in mixture and fry in deep fat.

title: poor man's abalone
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper; pound until 1/4-inch thick.
Place clam juice with garlic into casserole dish.
Place pounded breasts into juice.
Cover with foil and refrigerate for 36 hours.
Dredge each breast into flour and fry in butter about 3 minutes on each side.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie pie a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Soften cream cheese; add 1/2 cup sugar; mix well.
Spread over cookie bake that has been cooled.
Arrange fruit on top.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Shred in bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion in a large skillet, breaking up meat as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In a small saucepan, heat soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients.
Cover casserole tightly with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours in preheated 350° oven.

title: florentine salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Thaw spinach in pot of hot water; drain.
Pour cold water over to avoid overcooking.
Just before gelatin sets, mix spinach, mayonnaise, cottage cheese, vinegar, celery and onion.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish or mold and chill until set.

title: german meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form small meat balls (size of golf ball).
Bring bouillon and water to a boil.
Turn down and drop in meat balls.
Simmer (not boil) for 15 minutes.
Should be done in single layer so you may have to do 2 times (I use a large frypan).
Remove balls.
Thicken bouillon for gravy.
Pour over meat balls.
Keep warm until ready to serve.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Put vinegar in 1 cup cold water and mix with all ingredients; bake at 350° in glass 9 x 9-inch pan a few minutes.
Easy and good!

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pecans, in a bowl; toss gently to mix well.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or with whole grain bread for sandwiches.
Garnish with pecans, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: garlic balls
directions: Chop garlic into little pieces.
Mix garlic, oil, parsley and salt in bowl. Cut pizza dough into little balls and place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown, turning once.
When baked, mix garlic mixture and balls and serve warm.

title: pink lemonade grilled chicken
directions: Mix lemonade, soy and garlic. Marinate chicken in mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Cook chicken on charcoal grill for 15 minutes or until done. Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad deluxe
directions: Cook and dice chickens and mix with all ingredients except cheese and onions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and onions and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Stew chicken; reserve broth.
Cook noodles in broth; save broth.
Chop celery, onion and pepper.
Make layers of 1/2 of the noodles, soups, celery, green pepper, onion and chicken.
Repeat. Top with another layer.
Add cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy zucchini soup
directions: In saucepan bring potatoes to boil; reduce heat.
Cover. Simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Peel and cut into chunks.
Set aside. In large saucepan, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion and zucchini.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Transfer mixture to blender or food processor.
Add parsley; puree until almost smooth.
Add milk.
Serve hot or chilled.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: fall salad with parmesan dressing
directions: In small jar, combine lemon juice, 1/2 salt and 1/4 pepper. Shake until salt dissolves.
Add oil and grated cheese.
Shake again to combine.
Tear lettuce leaves into pieces; trim fennel and slice.
Combine the lettuce, fennel slices and olives; toss with dressing just before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, no longer (set timer for 8 minutes only).
Let cool completely.

title: regular pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix well all ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese in microwave or allow to soften at room temperature.
Combine with minced onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Pick through crab meat for shells.
Add crab meat to cream cheese mixture.

title: creole liver
directions: Brown flour dredged in liver fat.
Remove.
Saute onion and bell pepper in
remaining fat until tender.
Pour off any excess fat.
Add liver, tomatoes, water and seasonings to onion and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add extra water, if needed, while simmering.
Serves 6.

title: angel cookies
directions: Roll in balls. Dip in sugar. Bake at 375°.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together (except cheese).
In a buttered casserole layer macaroni mixture and shredded cheese.
Continue layering until all is used, saving plenty of cheese for top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cheese on top is melted.

title: amish apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Start with cold oven. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Spreads Ricotta cheese over crust.
In an 8-inch nonstick skillet, heat 2 teaspoons margarine until bubbly.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic until soft.
Add ground beef, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Spread mixture over Ricotta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with 2 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper.
Mix all ingredients except almonds and paprika.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, 3/4 stick margarine, nutmeg, milk and cinnamon with mixer.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300° or until about firm.
Melt remaining butter, brown sugar, pecans and corn flake crumbs.
Spread over souffle. Bake for 15 minutes more.
Yields 6 servings.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Cut vegetables as you prefer for stew. Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven. Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: eggnog chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup of the eggnog.
Heat the remaining 1 1/2 cup eggnog in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks slightly and stir in 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Pour a small amount of hot eggnog over egg yolks and mix well.
Return to eggnog in pan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats a spoon.

title: tangy mustard cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Add water; cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Combine mayonnaise, onion and mustard in small mixing bowl.
Spoon on top of cauliflower. Sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on Roast for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes to melt cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.

title: pineapple glazed carrots
directions: In medium saucepan combine carrots, pineapple with syrup, water and seasoning blend.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until carrots are tender.
In a small cup blend butter and flour to make a roux.
Stir roux into carrots in orange juice and simmer 1 minute.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli partially.
Lay in bottom of casserole.
Put chicken on top.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayonnaise together and put on top of chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then bread crumbs, then melted butter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven; cover to bake.

title: lite punch bowl cake
directions: In punch bowl, break angel food cake up into small pieces. Then you layer the fruit in the order they are listed.
You mix pudding as directed on the package and pour over the fruit.
Serve with Cool Whip.
However, it is optional.
Served with Cool Whip, this recipe has 50 optional calories.
This is a Weight Watchers recipe.

title: chocolate mint ice cream pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream into the pie crust.
Freeze 1 to 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with chocolate curls and fresh mint leaves, if desired.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using only the tender parts of the broccoli and cauliflower (no stalks).

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Combine all liquids and add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir, mixing well.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Stir together the first four ingredients.
Do not heat.
Pour this mixture over the cukes and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: jonna's delight
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown ground meat and onion.
Mix together. Add cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 can milk.
Mix all together and serve with salad and vegetables.
Fast and easy for a working Mom.

title: crazy crust peach cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter or margarine in a square Pyrex dish.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk in a bowl. Strain juice off peaches and retain juice.
Pour peaches only in buttered cooking dish.
Sprinkle the different spices lightly over the peaches.
Pour batter evenly over peaches.
Pour peach juice on top of butter.
Sprinkle spices on top of peach juice.
Cook in oven at 350°.
Cobbler is done when the crust is brown and has a cake texture.

title: smothered steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Flour meat.
Put meat and sliced onion in large skillet with enough oil to cook.
When meat is done, remove meat and onion from skillet.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in large bowl, flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, oil and eggs, then add to dry ingredients and mix together. Fold in carrots, pineapple, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake for 1 hour.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Once melted, combine all ingredients, except Ritz crackers.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain mixed vegetables and water chestnuts.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttery bubble bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and 1 cup of flour. Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place about 1 hour. Punch dough down. Turn onto a lightly floured surface; shape into 1 1/2-inch balls. Dip in butter and arrange evenly in a greased 9-inch fluted tube pan. Drizzle with remaining butter; cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool for 5 minutes before inverting onto a platter.

title: reese's peanut butter cup oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Add granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt; blend into peanut butter mixture.
Stir in oats.
Cover dough; refrigerate several hours or until firm enough to handle.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until almost set; cool 5 minutes.
Remove wrappers from peanut butter cups and place one on each cookie, pressing down gently.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: cured venison hind quarter
directions: Step 1:
Debone hind quarter.
Weigh and calculate amount of quick cure to be used.
Place Quick Cure, pepper, spices and garlic in bowl and mix well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients. Mix together the next 5 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat well, then add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been well greased at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 1 large cake.

title: hot sauce
directions: Grind or blend all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; turn burner down and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with fork. Add sugar and salt. Let stand 15 minutes before using. Mix together dry ingredients. Stir together butter, eggs and vanilla. Add banana mixture. Mix well by hand. Stir in flour slowly. Fold in nuts. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until barely firm, not mushy.
Drain.
Melt cheese on top.
Add both cans of soup and onion.
Stir.
Place in a casserole dish.
Top with cornflakes.
Bake on 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown on top.

title: crock-pot hamburgers in sauce
directions: Shape beef in patties a bit thicker than your usual hamburger; meat will puff up in cooking. Place 1 layer in bottom of pot. Top with a layer of sauce. Place a second layer of patties. Add more sauce. Continue doing this until all patties and sauce are in the pot. Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: company's comin' brunch
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Place hash browns in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix well.
Let set in icebox overnight and then drain.
Ready to serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix banana cake mix, oil and eggs in large bowl on low speed. Cut up bananas and put in mix.
Add nuts and mix together.
Spray loaf pans with Pam and put mix in pans.
Cook at 275° until done. It should make 3 to 4 loaves of bread.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix sauce with the teriyaki sauce, tomato sauce, tomato paste, a can of water for each of the cans, brown sugar and onion soup mix.
Mix hamburger with the egg, breadcrumbs, onion and 1 cup sauce.
Make 1-inch diameter meatballs.
Bring sauce to a boil; add meatballs.
Slow-cook about 3 hours.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vinegar.
Fold in rhubarb and walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar if desired before baking.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Crumble the bread in baking dish. Beat together the eggs and milk. Add the cheese and sausage. Pour in baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: sandra's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain (can be cooked in microwave).
In a separate bowl, mix the other ingredients.
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine.
Add about 14 or more crushed saltine crackers (enough to thicken butter).
Put vegetables in casserole dish.
Add rest of ingredients and stir all together.
Pour melted butter with crushed crackers over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Will serve 6 to 8 people.

title: apple corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat together milk, egg and butter.
Add to dry ingredients with apples; stir just to moisten.
Grease 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: raisin and orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco together. Add eggs. Sift soda, flour and salt together. Add alternately with sour milk. Add raisins and ground orange. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 layers.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Boil and whip sweet potatoes ahead or use canned potatoes. Cream the sugar, eggs and oil.
Add water to dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 (9 x 5-inch) pans.
Fill pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Cook pork chops at 350° until brown (approximately 45 minutes).
Meanwhile, combine first 3 ingredients in a pot and cook until well blended (stir frequently).
Pour over pork chops and mix well with the drippings.
Cook another 45 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; cool. Place cheese slices on ham. Divide broccoli into 8 equal parts and place on ham and cheese slices. Roll up; place in dish. Mix soup, sour cream and mustard. Pour over rolled ham and broccoli. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Mash bananas; add lemon juice and mix.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Beat after each addition.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg into bowl; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs, sweet potatoes and water in bowl; blend well.
Add potato mixture all at once to dry ingredients, stirring just enough to moisten.
Pour batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans, lined with wax paper.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely; makes 2 loaves.

title: spaghetti alia oil(garlic and oil)
directions: Boil water for spaghetti, keep boiling.
Lightly brown garlic in oil, add anchovies, break with fork.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Cook and drain spaghetti and mix with oil and garlic sauce.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir.
After melted, add soup; blend.
Add rice and broccoli.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken in a 4-quart pot of water.
Skim top of water just before it comes to a boil.
The chicken takes about 1 1/2 hours to be tender.
Add vegetables the last 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles and add to the soup.

title: easy sparkling punch
directions: Prepare orange juice as directed on can.
Stir in lemon juice and corn syrup.
Slowly pour in ginger ale.
Serve in ice-filled glasses.

title: karen's kahlua dessert
directions: Cut cake into small squares.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Leave candy bars in wrapper and break with hammer into small pieces.
In glass bowl (because it looks pretty), layer:
cake, Kahlua, pudding, Cool Whip and chocolate pieces. Repeat layers.
Don't put last layer of Cool Whip until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Brown meat quickly in oleo.
Mix together salt, pepper and paprika and sprinkle over meat on both sides while frying.
Add the onion.
After browning, add 1 1/2 cups water or more, as needed. Put in bay leaves, cover and simmer for 1 hour or until tender. Remove meat from liquid.
Mix sour cream and flour together and add to broth, stirring rapidly until boiling.
Turn down to simmer, add chicken, cover and heat to boiling.
Serve with sauce over hot, drained noodles.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Slowly add sugar and continue beating until sugar is dissolved and mixture is very stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on foiled lined cookie sheet.
(Use two, a large one and a small one.) Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies in oven and close the door. Immediately turn off the thermostat.
Leave the cookies in the oven overnight.
Do not open the oven until the next morning.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and butter in pan.
Add all other ingredients to hamburger; cover and let simmer for 1 hour.
Left over pinto beans can be substituted for kidney beans.

title: mom's red rice
directions: Cook bacon in a medium size heavy saucepan until done.
Saute onion until soft.
Add canned tomatoes.
Use the can to measure 2/3 can (to the top set of inside ridges) of rice and 1/3 can water.
Add to mixture and bring to a boil.
Lower heat immediately.
Add a generous amount of salt and pepper and a half teaspoon of sugar.
Stir and cover.
Cook over low heat for approximately 1 hour, stirring with a fork every 10 minutes.
Rice should be firm and dry and not "crunchy."

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and steam.
Add vanilla after cooking.
Cook on top of stove slowly and carefully.
Can put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and cook in microwave.
Stir after each 5 minutes.
Cook approximately 20 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well in saucepan.
Cook until leaves sides of pan.
Remove and knead when cool.
Keep in airtight container (Ziploc bag).

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add salt and onion powder and stir well. Spread meat in bottom of casserole pan.
Layer 1 can carrots over meat.
Layer mashed potatoes over carrots.
Brush melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° until browned and warmed.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Combine milk, eggs, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Place bread in bottom of greased casserole dish. Add sausage to mixture and pour into dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: june bugs
directions: Mix cheese and butter; beat until smooth.
Mix the next 3 ingredients; add to cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Cut dates crosswise.
Wrap each half with dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 50 appetizers.

title: chocolate half-moon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in the order given.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for about 7 minutes.
Cool; frost half of flat side with white icing, half with chocolate icing.

title: ice cream confetti jello mold
directions: On the day before, mix red and lime jello separately with 1 1/2 cups boiling water each.
Chill.
The next day, mix lemon jello with 1 cup boiling water; cool 15 minutes.
(The rest of liquid for lemon jello is from the ice cream and crushed pineapple.)
Beat softened ice cream quickly with lemon jello and crushed pineapple so that the mixture is smooth.
Cube the red and lime jello and fold into ice cream mixture.
Pour into a 5-quart mold; put into refrigerator to set.
Yields 15 servings.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and sour cream together.
Layer:
chips, chicken (cubed or pieces), salsa, soup-sour cream mixture, cheeses (grated) and olives.
Repeat.
Bake 1 hour at 350° covered with foil.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add partially thawed strawberries.
Add crushed pineapple, including juice and diced bananas.
Pour half of mixture into a 12 x 15-inch pan.
When this is firm, spread 1 pint sour cream on top of it.
Pour rest of jello on top.
Let set until firm.

title: mom's no bake cookies
directions: Mix in a heavy saucepan butter, milk, cocoa, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add oats; mix well.
Spoon out onto wax paper to cool.

title: cheese and onion sandwich buns
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast from hot roll mix in water. Stir in remaining ingredients; add flour mixture.
Blend well. Cover and let rise until double in size.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Spry or Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas and vanilla and mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in milk.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes in regular dripping pan at 350°.

title: german potato apple stew
directions: Melt butter in a large covered saucepan.
Saute onion in butter until golden.
Stir in flour, gradually add broth, apple juice, lemon juice, salt and caraway seed, stirring until thickened.
Add potatoes, ham, prunes and bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add apples, cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes and apples are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter. Melt butter in aluminum pie pan. Pour butter into mixture. Pour mixture back into pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: ham and barley soup
directions: In large pot, brown celery, carrots and onions in 2 tablespoons oil.
Remove from pan.
Brown turnips and mushrooms in 2 more tablespoons oil.
Return carrot mixture.
Add ham bone, barley, thyme, salt, pepper, bouillon and 12 cups water to the pot; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Cut meat from bone and into small pieces.
Return ham; add stewed tomatoes and beans to pot.
Heat to boiling.
Cover; simmer on low 5 to 10 minutes, until beans are tender.
Serves 10.

title: microwave pizza casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, pepper and onion in 3-quart dish. Microwave on High for 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except cheeses.
Cook, covered on High for 15 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Top with cheeses.
Cook on High 1 minute to melt.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate dessert crepes
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat with rotary beater until blended. Heat a greased 6-inch skillet; remove from heat.
Add 2 tablespoons batter; lift and tilt skillet to spread batter.
Return to heat, browning on one side (or cook with inverted crepe pan).
Invert over paper towel.
Remove crepe.
Repeat to make 16 to 18, greasing skillet each time.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix together the kraut, onion, sweet pepper, celery and carrots.
In pan, mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper. Heat until sugar melts.
Pour over kraut mixture and chill.

title: easy oven fudge
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 1/2-quart ovenproof bowl, first put in milk, whole oleo stick and cocoa powder.
Dump in powdered sugar over top.
Don't stir.
Place in oven, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes (or until oleo is completely melted).
Remove and add vanilla. Beat with electric mixer on high 2 to 3 minutes or until smooth.
(Add nuts now if desired.)
Spread in buttered 8-inch pan. Refrigerate until firm.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes and green onions finely. Add cilantro and remaining ingredients to tomato mixture and mix gently. Cover and chill until ready to serve. Makes 1 cup.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes on low speed. Pour into three greased and floured round cake tins.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring to a boil the brown sugar, milk and margarine.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: apple pie squares
directions: Cut up apples and place in 9X13 glass pan.
Sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
In a bowl, combine 2 c. sugar, flour, eggs, butter, vanilla and salt.
Pour over apples.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Add beaten eggs and blend well.
Stir in milk.
Let cook slowly, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Let cool.
Add evaporated milk, vanilla, peaches and remaining 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Fill freezer bucket.
Add enough whole milk to fill to freezer line. Freeze.
Makes one gallon.

title: unshrink a sweater
directions: Dissolve non-iodized salt in warm water.
Cover garment with solution and soak for 3 hours.
Wash in mild soap and water. Rinse in water containing instant hair conditioner.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package; drain.
Combine butter, cheese, half and half, salt and pepper.
Toss with noodles and serve.

title: strawberry "salad"
directions: Stir jello and boiling water until dissolved.
Add strawberries; stir until thawed.
Add crushed pineapple. Refrigerate until set.

title: strawberry cake
directions: To cake mix, add flour, then add Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve jello in warm water; cool and add to cake mixture.
Add strawberries.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) pans at 350° about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix tomato soup, onion, green pepper, garlic and chicken broth; cook over low heat until tender.
Add mushroom soup, chopped chicken, a small jar pimiento and Velveeta cheese.
Stir over very low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir sauce and 1 small package of cooked, thin spaghetti together and pour into a large Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Keep warm in oven until serving time.

title: carolina chew cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients except powdered sugar.
Spoon batter into a well-greased and lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Cool.
Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together; pour melted oleo in mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Pour into a deep dish pie shell or 2 regular pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce the temperature to 325° and bake for about 30 minutes more.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar; blend in egg, peanut butter, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate chips; let stand 5 minutes.

title: cowboy corn bread
directions: Melt shortening in iron skillet.
Mix ingredients.
Add the melted shortening.
Mix well.
Pour in hot pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown in 400° oven.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, water and pineapple together and put in 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: up-north caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in grocery bag that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Combine sugar, syrup and butter in a bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave (2 to 4 minutes).
Stir in soda.
Pour this hot mixture into the bag with the popped corn.
Shake.
Close bag and microwave 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Shake.
Microwave 30 seconds.
Shake.
Microwave 30 seconds. Shake; pour onto waxed paper to cool.
Ready to eat in minutes.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt like pie crust.
Add egg yolk and milk to make 3/4 cup, beat, add to flour mixture.
Roll out and cover a 10 x 15-inch pan or cookie sheet, use 1/2 of pie crust. Mix together cornflakes, sugar and apples.
Spread on top of crust. Cover apple mixture with other 1/2 of pie crust mixture.
Beat egg white and sugar, spread over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oh-so-easy tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook noodles according to package directions. Drain noodles and leave in cooking pot. Add mushrooms, onion, tuna and cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Spray a 2-quart casserole dish or pan with butter-flavor Pam. Add tuna/noodle mixture. (If desired, 1 tablespoon butter or margarine can be added before baking.) Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: 60 minute yeast rolls(a very fast yeast roll recipe; ready in less than an hour.)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; place milk, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan and heat to lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour and leave in warm place for 15 minutes.
Turn out on floured board and pat to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut with round biscuit cutter.
Fold dough over a bit of butter to form Parker House rolls.
Let rise in warm place on a baking sheet for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut carrot salad
directions: Put all together in a large bowl and stir well.
The longer it sits, the better it gets.
Very good.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Beat water, sugar, yeast, 2 cups flour and salt until smooth. Add eggs, oil and 4 1/2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Punch down.
Knead on floured board.
Shape into rolls. Let rise 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Butter tops. These may be frozen and keep well.

title: coconut potato fudge
directions: Boil potatoes, drain and wash.
Add powdered sugar and melted butter.
Add coconut.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let set until firm.
Melt chocolate squares and pour over fudge mixture.
Let set until hard.
Cut in squares.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and place in oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch or larger).

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Cook the potato in the water. Run the potato and water through strainer.
Let cool and add the remaining ingredients.
Put in large bowl.
Keep in refrigerator, taking out enough dough each time to make the number of biscuits desired. Brush with butter. Let rise.
Bake at 450°.
Good like rolls.

title: osgood pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add pecans and raisins.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° until it begins to brown, then reduce oven temperature to 300°, cover with foil and cook until done.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Cream together ingredients and chill for 1 hour.
Put 1 big spoonful of mixture on flour tortillas, spread out and roll up. Chill for 1 hour, then slice into pieces.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour a bundt pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped PECANS.
Pour batter over pecans in pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for one hour to 1 hour, 10 minutes.
Let cool 20 minutes. Pour GLAZE over cake while still in the pan.
Do not remove cake from pan until completely cool.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dice apples into a large mixing bowl.
Pour sugar and lemon juice over them.
Stir and set aside while mixing the other ingredients.

title: filet of trout
directions: Dip filets in milk; roll in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and cayenne.
Dip in milk again and coat with bread crumbs.
In a large skillet, over high heat, melt butter and brown filets on both sides.
Remove to a heated serving platter.
Lower heat.
Add mushrooms, artichokes and parsley and cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in wine.
The mixture will bubble and turn slightly dark.
Spoon sauce over fish and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: bean bake
directions: Combine hot dogs, beans, catsup, water and mustard in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Stir in corn meal.
Add egg, milk, oil and onion all at once to sifted dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to combine.
Spoon mixture over beans.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Combine oil, brown or white sugar and beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with warm milk, sugar and cinnamon.
Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients, in order given, adding eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except almonds.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use more broth if dry.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice the apples thin. Sprinkle the cinnamon and sugar over the apples.
Mix the butter, flour and brown sugar until coarse. Put this mixture on top of the apples. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, cake coloring, margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda and vinegar and mix into cake mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 375° in layer pans (greased) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with your favorite cream cheese icing.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix flour, salt, oregano, pepper, eggs and milk.
Pour into greased and floured pizza pan.
Arrange meats, onion and mushrooms on top.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Combine sauce, oregano and pepper and spread on top of baked pizza.
Spread cheese on.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, coconut and chocolate chips. Beat 2 minutes; fold in other ingredients.
Pour into prepared Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake at 325° until done.
Cool 1 hour.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
1/2 cup boiling water.
Heat applesauce and
add
to
jello.
Mix; add pecans and chill in an 8 x 10-inch flat pan.
Serve in squares.
Easy and nice to use when color is needed to add interest to a meal.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix butter, milk, salt and sugar.
Melt in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Mix yeast with 1/2 cup warm water and let foam.
Mix all ingredients and let rise for 5 hours in a warm spot.
Punch down. Make rolls and let rise again.
Then bake in a 350° oven.
May keep spare dough in refrigerator after punched down until ready to use.

title: chocolate coconut crunches
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine and eggs; mix well.
Add coconut, walnuts, cornflakes, rolled oats and chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon at 2-inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until set. Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: best-ever meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Top with can of tomato sauce with green peppers and onions added. Return to oven just until this gets good and hot.

title: mom's quickie peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook and stir first 4 ingredients until marshmallows are melted.
Stop cooking at this stage and add peanut butter and beat until thick enough to pour into a greased pan (size of pan depends on how thick you like your fudge).
Yummy!

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Saute onion in margarine; stir in stuffing.
Remove from heat. Add liquid and mix.
Wrap one teaspoonful in 1/2 strip of bacon. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until bacon cooks.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add carrots, bananas and nuts.
Mix in eggs.
Put in greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add butternut vanilla, salt and milk alternately with flour.
Finally add cherries and nuts.
Start in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: oven roasted veggies
directions: *Use sliced zucchini, green pepper and carrots.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces.
Put in crock-pot.
Pour onion and mushroom soups over steak.
Add water.
Season to taste.
Cook on high until it starts boiling.
Turn down to low and cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: skillet recipe swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 4 serving pieces.
Trim fat.
Combine flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
With a meat mallet, pound flour mixture into meat.
In a large skillet, brown meat on both sides in hot oil.
Drain fat.
Add undrained tomatoes, onion, celery, carrot and thyme.
Cover and cook over low heat about 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Skim fat.
Serve with hot rice or noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
In large bowl, combine sugar, salt and 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour in hot milk.
Stir until butter is melted and sugar dissolved.
Stir in yeast.
Beat in egg.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Roll out dough to an 18 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with butter.

title: "toastem party squares"
directions: Melt margarine and cheeses; fold in egg whites, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip bread cubes in this mixture, then place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(low in fat and cholesterol)
directions: Melt margarine in a 10-inch black iron skillet.
Add brown sugar and mix until smooth.
Lay pineapple slices in mixture (don't overlap) (save juice for liquid in cake mix).
Place a maraschino cherry in the center of each pineapple ring.

title: spicy corn and beans
directions: Put onion in a microwavable casserole, covered, and microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat butter until light and fluffy. Gradually add about half of the powdered sugar, beating well. Beat in milk and the vanilla.
Gradually beat in remaining powdered sugar, then add milk, if necessary, to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Frost tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. In a large bowl, stir together pineapple chunks and marshmallows, cover and chill for up to 24 hours. Meanwhile, for dressing, in a small saucepan, stir together the sugar and all purpose flour. Add reserved pineapple juice, vinegar and egg. Cook and stir over medium heat just until mixture bubbles, reduce heat. Cook and stir for 2 minutes more. Transfer the mixture to a small bowl. Cover the surface of the mixture with plastic wrap and chill. To serve, add chilled dressing, apples, dessert topping, cherries and peanuts to marshmallow mixture, stir to mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs and bananas.
Beat together.
Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well.
Bake in 2 small greased bread pans or 1 large greased bread pan 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: helen's chocolate cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar and add eggs.
Alternate buttermilk with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and soda-water mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased pan and bake 40 minutes at 325° or until done, depending upon size of pan.
Does not need frosting.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, allspice and baking soda together. Dust raisins and nuts with a small amount of the flour mixture. Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy. Beat in egg.
Add flour mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in raisins, nuts and pineapple.
Pour in nonstick 9-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for several minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Yields 16 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Mix all other ingredients and place on top of apples. Bake until brown at 375°.

title: basil jelly
directions: Bruise 1 cup of basil.
Add to 2 cups of water, cider vinegar and lemon juice.
Steep 20 minutes.
Strain.
Discard the basil leaves.
To the water add 6 cups of sugar.
Bring to a full boil. Stir constantly until sugar dissolves.
When at a full boil, add 1 packet of liquid pectin.
Boil 1/2 minute more.
Remove from heat; add green food coloring.
Pour into sterilized hot jars and seal. Make 3 pints.
Good with lamb or chicken.

title: ultimate sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and Crisco in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Beat until blended and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture. Mix until well blended.
Divide into 4 quarters.
(Tip:
If dough is too sticky or too soft to roll, wrap each 1/4 of dough with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.)

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring butter, cream and sugar to boil.
Cook over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 7 minutes.
Before removing from heat, test by dropping a little in cold water.
If this forms into soft ball, then remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix well and pour into buttered dish.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Break each graham cracker in half.
Thaw the Cool Whip until soft.
Place 1/2 of the graham crackers in a cookie sheet and top with a spoonful of Cool Whip.
Top with another cracker and add Cool Whip on top.
You may add another layer, if you wish.
Repeat with other crackers.
Freeze for several hours.
When serving, top with a drizzle of chocolate sauce or other ice cream sauce.

title: jiffy hamburger stew
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off fat.
Cook vegetables according to directions.
Add hamburger, tomato juice and tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until bubbling.

title: curried rice
directions: In saucepan, cook onion with curry in butter until tender; toss with rice.
Serve chicken over rice; garnish with parsley.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Stir all ingredients in large glass bowl.
Dump into Pam coated casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with butter and thinly sliced toast made from French bread or with bagel chips.
If cooked in crock pot, cook on high for one hour.

title: cabbage and hamburger bake
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Place hamburger with the onion and stir in uncooked rice.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage and then cover with the soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, garlic, basil, parsley, salt, red and green pepper and Parmesan cheese in large bowl.
Mix pasta with fresh vegetables, cut into bite size.
Add cheese and pepperoni.
Stir in dressing.

title: pear salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1 cup hot water.
Add juice from pears and pineapple, 1/4 cup sugar and juice from 1/2 lemon. Heat. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add fruit.
Cool.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish. Chill until firm.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute onion in oil and drain.
Mix and use juices of pork and beans, navy beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, sugar, catsup, mustard and pepper.
Mix all together and stir well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken breast in sour cream
directions: Chop beef finely and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Wrap each piece of chicken on its own bed of chipped beef.
Mix together the undiluted soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: caramel squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, then add chips and nuts.
Bake in a greased 13 x 11 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese croissants
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic over medium-high heat, stirring frequently until onion is translucent, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in spinach, Ricotta, Mozzarella cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg until thoroughly combined.
Preheat oven to 350°. Separate dough; place 3 tablespoons of mixture on wide end of each roll.
Roll up to form croissant; place on nonstick baking sheet. Repeat with remaining rolls.
Bake until golden, about 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: breakfast sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Put in bottom of ungreased glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle bread on top of sausage, then do the same with the cheese.
In bowl, mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over top in baking dish.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: microwave swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle half of flour on one side of meat; pound in with rolling pin or meat mallet.
Turn meat and sprinkle with remaining flour; pound with rolling pin.
Cut into 4 serving size pieces. Arrange in 8-inch square microwave baking dish.
In small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour over meat. Cover tightly with microwave-safe plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium for 12 to 17 minutes or until meat is almost tender.
Let stand, tightly covered, for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together brown sugar, white sugar, Crisco and water.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix again.
Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix again.
Add oatmeal.
Mix again.
Refrigerate before spooning onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool at least 1 minute before serving, better consistency.

title: easy easter eggs
directions: You can color your eggs as
you hard-boil them.
Add 15 to 20 drops food coloring plus 1 tablespoon vinegar, using an enamel pan is best.
Repeat procedure with other colors.
Use color straight from bottle.
Try these blends.
Purple:
15 drops red and 5 drops blue.
Chartreuse:
12 drops yellow and 1 drop green.
Turquoise: 15 drops blue and 5 drops green.
Orange:
12 drops yellow and 6 drops red.
Teal:
12 drops green and 6 drops blue.

title: south carolina chews
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder. Mix until crumbly.
Add eggs, vanilla and nuts; mix.
Spread in a greased, floured 14 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar over chews while warm.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 16 large servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Blend all dry ingredients together.
Add to butter mixture milk alternately with flour mixture.
Pour into floured and greased spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Combine pudding and Bisquick.
Add oil and egg; stir.
Mix in milk, coconut and extract.
Roll into teaspoonful balls; place on cookie sheet and slightly flatten.
Bake at 275° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle tops with sugar, if desired.
Yield:
20 cookies.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Blend butter and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and enough milk to make frosting soft enough to spread.
Decorate top of cake with pitted dates.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Cook pudding as directed on box except increase the milk to 3 cups.
Cool. Freeze in popsicle molds or small waxed paper cups. Insert sticks into paper cup molds when partially frozen. To serve, peel off paper cup.

title: boiled white frosting
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and cook with cream of tartar and salt to soft ball stage.
Add syrup to egg white, beating constantly. Beat in flavoring and beat until thick enough to spread.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Blend with dry ingredients.
Stir in grated zucchini. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: nacho topper
directions: Season meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Cook and drain meat. Add tomatoes and cheese, stirring constantly.
Do not add Pet milk until ready to serve.
Heat and serve over nacho chips.

title: apple chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and simmer until fruit is soft, about a half hour if the apples are crisp.
Serve warm or cold.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup; add milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Blend flour, salt and Tabasco sauce.
Add milk mixture and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Flake salmon and add to sauce with lemon juice.
Stir in 1/2 cup corn flake crumbs.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Divide mixture into 8 or 10 portions; shape each portion into a cone.
Roll cones in remaining 1/2 cup corn flake crumbs to coat well.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve croquettes with Tabasco Tartar Sauce or a commercial tartar sauce.
Yields 8 to 10 croquettes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown your beef or turkey; drain off all fat.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, put the Fritos on the bottom.
Next, rinse kidney beans and lay on top of Fritos. Next, heat refried beans in saucepan with butter; add on top of kidney beans.
Add cheese to the top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together; form into bars and freeze overnight.
Cut and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: low calorie cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly butter bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Combine crumbs, 2 teaspoons sugar and butter. With the back of a large spoon, press onto the bottom and sides of pan.
Bake 5 minutes.
Blend cottage cheese, dry milk, 1/3 cup sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla extract until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake until firm, about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; spread yogurt on top.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving, top with washed, dry strawberries.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer: Melt 1 stick margarine. Mix with crumbs and spread over bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: creamed macaroni meat bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. In a bowl combine sour cream, cottage cheese and egg.
Mix. Stir in cooked macaroni.
In a 2-quart baking dish, layer half of macaroni mixture, then half of meat mixture.
Repeat.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.

title: amoree
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper and set aside.
Cook spaghetti as directed; drain.
Mix meat mixture and spaghetti.
Add soups; mix well.
Pour in baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put catsup on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Then turn oven down to about 325° and cook for about 1 hour.

title: papa's favorite spaghetti dish
directions: Boil and bone chicken and set aside. Saut green onions in butter, then add chili powder, soups and olives. Boil spaghetti. Add this and chopped chicken to soup mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt Hershey bars using a double boiler or simply take a pot of water and bring to a boil and place a pan over the top of pot and melt chocolate.
This is to ensure that your chocolate does not burn up.
Mix until well blended the melted chocolate and the container of Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Allow 1 hour for refrigeration.

title: brown sugar crust
directions: Crush cornflakes; set aside.
Beat butter and brown sugar at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add yolks, salt and almond extract, beating until smooth.
Gradually add flour and cereal.
Shape mixture into a ball; press into a well buttered 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden.
Cool completely.

title: homemade cranberry sauce
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to bowl.
Add cranberries.
Cook until cranberries start to pop open.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: stracciatella(italain egg ribbon soup)
directions: In a saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients; bring it to boil. Turn heat down and let simmer.
In a bowl, combine eggs, salt, pepper and cheese; beat vigorously.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Turn heat up on broth and whisk in egg mixture until egg ribbons form. Work quickly.
Serve hot! Serves 4.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and Cool Whip thoroughly.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: percolator hot fruit tea(makes the house smell wonderful.)
directions: Pour first 5 ingredients into percolator; add brown sugar. Place cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger into percolator basket.

title: chicken and cashews
directions: Stir together soy sauce, cornstarch and water.
Set aside.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil and pour into the remaining six ingredients.
Batter will be very thin.
Pour into a sheet cake pan or a 9 x 12-inch (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
The 9 x 12-inch may take 25 minutes, depending on your oven.
Check with a toothpick.
While cake is baking, prepare icing.

title: deep-dish peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in deep baking dish.
Mix sugar, baking powder, salt, flour and milk; pour into melted butter.
Do not stir.
Put peaches on top and do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate; shape into bars or balls.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Take out a few at a time and dip into melted dipping chocolate.
Place on waxed paper; refrigerate again until set.

title: virginia sweet pickles
directions: Boil and pour over pickles.
On fifth morning, reheat the vinegar solution; add 2 cups sugar and pour over pickles.
On sixth morning, reheat vinegar.

title: deviled hamburgers
directions: In heavy skillet, put oil.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery which has been finely chopped.
Cook and stir for about 3 minutes. Add hamburger meat.
Cook until it loses its pink color, about 10 minutes.
Add tomato soup and water; stir well.
Cover.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour.
When done, spoon on hamburger buns, which have been toasted, and spread with mayonnaise.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables in pieces.
Mix other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: southern stew
directions: Cut ham into 1/2 inch
cubes and set aside.
Cook onion and garlic in shortening until tender.
Add ham and brown lightly; pour off drippings.
Add green pepper, lemon, pepper, thyme, tomatoes, rice and water.
Cover tightly and simmer 25 or 30 minutes or until rice is fluffy.
Yields 10 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat ingredients to boiling, pour over jars which have been packed with cucumbers and dill, garlic and dried peppers.
It usually takes a couple pieces of garlic and 4-5 peppers to give it a good `bite'.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each piece of chicken and lay on the beef. Combine sour cream and mushroom soup and spread over chicken. Cover with foil and bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir until well mixed.
Cook over low-medium heat.
Bring to boil and boil gently 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir and chill until set.

title: spicy beans and rice(makes 6 servings.)
directions: Heat a nonstick skillet.
Add oil.
Add onion, garlic, zucchini and carrot.
Cook over low heat until vegetables are soft.
Add salsa and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in beans, rice and seasonings.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese and heat until cheese melts.
Contains 164 calories per serving.

title: creme center chocolates
directions: Mix margarine, salt, cream and 1/2 of the sugar with mixer until blended.
Unless you have a mixer with dough hook, continue kneading in remaining sugar by hand.
Mixture will be very stiff. If making all one flavor, add at first.
If making a variety, divide and use flavorings accordingly.
Shape into desired shapes. Chill.
Dip in chocolate coating.

title: kielbasa and beans
directions: In a skillet cook sausage 2-3 minutes.
Stir in onions and peppers.
Cook and stir until sausage is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Combine brown sugar, steak sauce, vinegar and worcestershire sauce.
Stir into skillet.
Add beans, cook and stir until heated.
4 servings.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together, then spread onto English muffins.
Freeze for a few hours or overnight.
Cut into fourths while frozen.
Put under broiler until bubbly.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer or blender for 5 minutes.
Put in quart jar with 1 onion and 2 garlic cloves.
Take onion and garlic out after 3 or 4 days.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put chicken in pan of water.
Put in tarragon, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Boil about 20 to 30 minutes. Take chicken out of pan and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, curry powder, mayonnaise and milk.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients in a glass bowl. Cook in microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool in refrigerator. Cut into squares.

title: fasolatha(bean soup)
directions: Soak beans
in	cold water overnight.
If you forget to do this, then	cover beans with water; let them come to a boil for about 2
minutes.
Take
off
fire	and cover beans for an hour. Drain; rinse beans and make soup.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cake is done when toothpick comes back clean.
For softer raisins, boil them in water for 1 minute and drain.
Bake at 350° for 45 or more minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Place in large bowl.
Add sugar and cinnamon; cover and shake until well coated.
Pour in Bundt pan and pour melted butter over biscuits evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana-caramel pie
directions: Bring milk still in can to a gentle boil for 3 hours.
Keep can covered with water while cooking.
Let cool 3 hours.
Open can at both ends.
Slice bananas in a baked pie crust and pour caramelized milk from can onto pie.
Cover with whipped cream and nuts.
Very rich.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls then flatten into cakes.
Heat olive oil in skillet.
Brown well on both sides.

title: carmelized nuts
directions: Place sugar, water and nuts in a 7-inch skillet and begin with high heat.
After stirring several minutes, the nuts will crystallize.
Turn down heat to low, and continue stirring.
The nuts are finished carmelizing after they have a shiny glaze on them.
After the nuts cool, break them apart.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into a roll and wrap in wax paper.
Place in refrigerator for 4 hours before slicing.

title: apple goodie(crisp)
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Mix together the sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and cinnamon.
Put sliced apples into this mixture and toss them together.
Place in bottom of baking pan which has been greased and floured, then mix remaining ingredients.
