Work 1/2 cup oleo into this mixture and spread in a layer on top of the apples. Bake at 350° until apples are done and topping is golden brown. Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Melt together in double boiler or microwave the remaining 2 ingredients.
Pour over cereal mixture and stir well until all cereal is coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let set until firm.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream shortening and butter until very soft, add sugar and cream well.
Add vanilla.
Measure nuts, then chop very fine (use blender or food processor). Combine with flour and stir creamed mixture.
Form into small balls, place them on ungreased baking sheet and bake in slow oven at 300° for about 45 minutes.
Roll while hot in powdered sugar.
When cold, roll again in powdered sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: pita bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and stir in honey and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Knead dough for several minutes and then cut into 8 pieces.
Knead each piece several minutes.
Roll or shape into 5-inch round pieces about 1/2-inch thick.
Let rise 2 hours. Bake at 500° for 8 minutes.
Makes 8 pita breads.
Share with your friends!

title: barbecue seasoning
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container. Rub onto chicken, steaks or hamburgers before grilling.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off the top of the peppers and clean them off; set aside. Mix ground beef, onions, garlic, rice, oregano and egg.
Stuff into peppers, top with jar of spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Mix and serve immediately.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick cake
directions: Beat 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in a greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Heat milk until it bubbles around edges.
Add shortening.
Remove from heat and cool. Add liquids to dry ingredients and mix on medium speed 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup of flour to thicken.
Add eggs and beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Flour cabinet; pour dough out and knead 15 to 20 minutes.
(Keep in refrigerator until ready to bake.)
Remove from bowl; roll out on floured cabinet and cut.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 375°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; then drain.
Stir in soup, taco sauce and seasonings.
Layer meat and rice alternately in casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good and easy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Chop eggs and onion.
Add spinach and soup to eggs and onion.
Mix in mayonnaise. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: yogurt or sour cream dressing
directions: Mix well and serve over tossed salads.
Great over lettuce and tomatoes.

title: german pancake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Melt 6 tablespoons margarine in a cake pan or cast-iron skillet in oven.
Beat
one minute, then pour into hot butter, the ingredients.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Top with powdered sugar and lemon juice if desired.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Combine the above ingredients in a large casserole dish. Place the Spanish rice on the bottom of the dish, then place the Ranch Style beans on top.
Next, spoon the ground beef over the beans, ending with the grated cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.

title: mexican seven layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip on the bottom of a 9 1/2 x 12-inch (or as close as possible) glass dish.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix together.
Spread over the bean dip.
Next sprinkle with onions (to your taste), tomatoes, olives and top with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips!!!

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs until light. Add mashed bananas and vanilla. Mix well. Set aside. Mix flour (not sifted), baking powder, soda and salt. Stir to blend. Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in nutmeats. Pour into 2 greased 9-inch layer pans or a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Put in 1 cup uncooked rice, onion soup mix and water; lay meat on top.
Cover with lid or foil. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Boil water and margarine.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour; mix well.
Pour over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (bakes uneven!); let cool.
Mix boxes of pudding and milk together.
Add cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Spread over cake, cover with Cool Whip and drizzle chocolate syrup over top.
Swirl and refrigerate.
Keep chilled.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in 2-quart casserole dish.
Add onion soup, rice and broth.
Add salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Cut margarine into pieces over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix
together and use different fruits to make a pretty party plate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix oleo and eggs.
Mix sugar and cocoa together, then into butter and eggs.
Add milk slowly while beating on low speed with mixer.
Add vanilla; pour into crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up lettuce in a bowl.
Cut up tomatoes, black olives, onion and cheese; add to lettuce.
Brown hamburger and add dry taco seasoning.
Add to cut up ingredients.
Mix together.
Great served over Doritos.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter pie plate.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread in the bottom of pie plate.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Mix crust and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Put dates and baking soda in boiling water and set aside to cool.
Add all other ingredients to the date mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 1/4 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger noodle bake
directions: Cook beef, onions, and peppers together and drain. Combine with meat and 2 c water; mix well and put in casserole dish. Toss 2 c soft bread crumbs and 1/4 c melted butter together, sprinkle on top casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° till heated through, about 45 min.

title: creamy reuben soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in water and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Add corned beef, sauerkraut, half and half and 1 cup of cheese.
Cook 30 minutes until slightly thickened, stirring frequently.
Ladle into 8 ovenproof bowls.
Top each with bread and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve immediately. Refrigerate leftovers.
Yield:
about 2 quarts.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown the flour in oil to make a smooth paste.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Stir until meat is coated with paste.
Add water and tomato sauce; mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours (or until tender).
Add vegetables and cook until tender.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and refrigerate. (Make several days before using.)
Salt and pepper chicken pieces. Place in pan, one layer deep.
Pour sweet sour mixture over chicken.
Bake 1 hour or until done in 350° oven.

title: banana orange muffins(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter or paper line muffin tins.

title: quick fix chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 7 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour undiluted soup over the chicken.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until tender.
Good with baked potatoes, steamed broccoli and raw vegetable plate.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Heat soup and butter until all melted. Do not dilute.
Heat this in a 10-inch skillet.
Then pour in 2 cups of rice. Mix well. Place 4 or 5 pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Cut off extra fat from the pork chops.
Spoon a little of the juice over chops. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, uncovered, or until pork chops are nice and brown on top.

title: rainbow dip
directions: In a platter, spread softened cream cheese with a spoon.
Add the jar of salsa; spread evenly.
Sprinkle the chopped green pepper on top of salsa.
Sprinkle chopped black olives on top of pepper.

title: refrigerator yeast dough
directions: Bring eggs and yeast to room temperature. Combine 3/4 cup of warm water, sugar, salt and shortening in mixing bowl. Dissolve yeast in the one cup of warm water (the temp of a baby's bottle). Stir into first mixture. Add eggs, 3 cups of flour and beat until smooth. Then stir in the 3 remaining cups of flour, this will be very stiff but keep stirring until flour is mixed in. Dough is now ready to use or store. It may be stored in the refrigerator in a greased, covered bowl.

title: honey beans
directions: Mix ingredients and put in microwave for about 20 minutes.

title: granny myers egg custard pie
directions: Beat together the eggs, milk and sugar.
Add the melted butter, vanilla and cinnamon or nutmeg.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes and then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes or until firm when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Watch carefully.

title: classic date bars
directions: Combine dates and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally for 3 to 4 minutes or until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Reserve.

title: lorene's brown rice
directions: Bring soups, butter and undrained mushrooms to boil in medium size saucepan.
Add rice, allow to return to boil, cover.
Turn off heat and let sit 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with fruit.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Heat potatoes, butter and sugar in saucepan.
Add vanilla and pineapple.
When cooled, mold around each marshmallow.
Roll in coconut.
Bake at 475° until coconut is golden brown.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and place in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over top of rhubarb. Bake at 375° until brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, garlic powder and oregano.
Heat in medium saucepan.
Let sit.
Dip eggplant in milk, then coat lightly with cornmeal; set aside.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Thaw the Cool Whip and mix the rest together; chill in refrigerator.

title: bread and butter pickles(keep in refrigerator)
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar (heat to make sugar and salt dissolve).
Add turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Put sliced cucumber and onion in gallon jar.
Pour liquid over them.
In 3 to 5 days they are ready to eat.
These will keep for months.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix butter with sugar, flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add slightly beaten egg, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Pat this mixture into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cajun rice
directions: Chop onions.
Add sausage and brown together in a large pan. Add mushrooms, beef bouillon and dry rice.
Cook together until rice is browned nicely.
Add 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook, covered, approximately 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in cottage cheese and melted margarine.
Stir in cornbread mix until well moistened.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Bake in a greased skillet approximately 30 minutes at 325°.

title: hearts of palm with capers vinaigrete
directions: Combine the mustard, salt and pepper to taste and the vinegar in a mixing bowl.
Using a wire whisk, gradually add the oil, beating vigorously.
Add the garlic and capers.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Makes 3 cups.
Combine fruit with orange liqueur or rum and sugar.
Serve immediately or refrigerate up to 8 hours before serving.

title: baked fish in cream
directions: Layer the bottom of baking dish with fish fillets.
Lightly sprinkle with salt and dry bread crumbs.
Carefully spread with cream and continue with layer of fish and then bread crumbs and cream.
Bake in oven at 325° until fish is tender, about 30 minutes.

title: chesapeake bay maryland crab soup
directions: Put 8 quarts of water in 24-quart canning pot and start cooking neck bones for approximately 2 hours.
Remove bones, return meat to stock and add steamed crabs that have had the outer shell removed and that have been cleaned and split in half and then split again across the middle, crack claws.
Dice potatoes, slice carrots, onions, celery and break beans and add to pot.
Cook 2 hours and then add rest of vegetables and seasonings.
Continue to simmer for 1 hour.
Makes approximately 6 gallons.

title: sunrise salsa
directions: Mix tomato paste with tomato sauce until paste dissolved.
Add white vinegar and red vinegar.
Chop all other ingredients and add to mix and mix well.
Add salt to taste.
Chill 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: ruth griffin's oatmeal cake
directions: Add boiling water to oatmeal.
Let cool for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining dry ingredients and oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat until light and fluffy. Add oil, dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and press with glass bottom dipped into sugar (or form into roll and chill and slice).
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 10 minutes).

title: venison stew 1
directions: Cut up the venison into 1-inch cubes.
Saute in bacon drippings until browned on all sides.
Add water to cover the meat, seasonings and onion.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook until carrots are tender.
Dissolve flour in some water to make a thin paste and stir it into the stew.
Cook for about 5 more minutes.

title: broiled peach halves
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spoon mincemeat into the center of each peach half.
Top with butter and broil.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Refrigerate in covered bowl overnight.
Put into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: five bean salad
directions: Empty all cans into a colander. Drain well. Combine beans, water chestnuts, onion and garlic in a bowl. Combine the rest of the ingredients and pour over bean mixture; stir well. Cover and chill for 2 to 4 hours.

title: cathedral wonder slices
directions: Melt together margarine and chocolate chips. Add slightly beaten eggs and blend well. Cool. Add marshmallows and pecans in a large mixing bowl. Pour chocolate mixture over pecans and marshmallows and stir well. Place about 1/2 cup powdered sugar on a sheet of waxed paper. Divide mixture in half and shape into a roll on the powdered sugar. Wrap in the waxed paper and place in the refrigerator overnight to chill. Repeat with remaining half of mixture.

title: zucchini honey bread
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar; set aside. Mix honey, oil, zucchini, eggs, nuts, vanilla and raisins and add to flour mixture.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar and corn syrup or honey; bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.
Great snack.

title: spaghetti cheese casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti, except microwave 9 minutes.
In small bowl, mix soup, milk, onion, pepper and olives.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of spaghetti, cheese and soup mixture. Microwave at High 9 to 12 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel bread pudding
directions: Combine the apples, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and butter in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes,
stirring frequently.
Add the apple juice, raisins, vanilla, evaporated milk, eggs, brown sugar and bread cubes, mixing well.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Process the walnuts with the remaining 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and sugar in a blender.
Sprinkle over the pudding.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: pork steak casserole
directions: Arrange pork steaks in baking dish.
Brown steaks in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Add rice and sprinkle with salt and pepper over top.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and onion.
Pour stock over top.
Place in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Cook 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli, garlic and oil over pasta
directions: Pour oil into Teflon frypan.
Slice or chop garlic and brown lightly in oil.
Add chopped broccoli to oil and stir occasionally.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes to desired tenderness. Pour over 1 pound cooked pasta and toss.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and all eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk. Gradually add prunes and nuts.
Bake in flat pan (9 x 13-inch) at 300° for 30
minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes. Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix all dry ingredients and put in paper sack. Shake potatoes in sack and place on side in melted oleo. Pour remaining dry ingredients from sack over potatoes. Sprinkle generously with paprika. Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour, uncovered, and do not turn potatoes while cooking.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat whites until stiff peaks form.
Gradually beat in brown sugar. Stir in vanilla.
Pile onto pie.
Bake at 325° until brown.

title: andrew's favorite puppy dogs(hush puppies)
directions: Combine well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil until golden brown.
Float to the top.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: *White cherries may be substituted.

title: christmas plum pudding
directions: Stone and cut raisins in half but do not chop them.
Wash. Pick and dry the currants and mince the suet finely.
Cut candied peel into thin slices and grate down the bread into fine crumbs. When all these dry ingredients are prepared, mix them all together with the sugar.
Then moisten the mixture with the eggs which should be well beaten.
Add the brandy; stir well.
Everything may be thoroughly blended and press the pudding into a buttered mould. Tie it down tightly with a floured cloth and boil 5 to 6 hours for the first boiling.
Two hours the day it is to be served it may be boiled in a cloth without a mould.

title: 6 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients.
Let set overnight and serve.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, buttermilk and syrup. Grease and sugar a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: garlic bread
directions: Spread bread with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Place bread slices, buttered side up, on broiler pan. Broil 3 to 4-inches from heat for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: the ultimate taco salad
directions: Brown ground meat and add taco seasoning according to directions.
Cool slightly.
In large bowl, add cheese, tomatoes, lettuce, salsa, ground meat, sour cream and 3/4 cup Italian dressing.
Stir all ingredients.
Add crushed chips before serving and stir in.
Or add chips separately in bowl to person's taste and add wet ingredients.

title: french coconut tarts
directions: Melt butter and sugar over heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Fill unbaked tart shells with coconut and ingredients.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Check centers to see when done.

title: sheet cake
directions: Combine oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water; bring to a boil. Combine
sugar, flour, buttermilk and pour boiled mixture over it. Add
eggs
and soda; mix well.
Bake in a large sheet pan for 20 minutes.

title: tropical pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients on low speed.
Beat 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Cool 15 minutes in pan; remove.
Drizzle with powdered sugar and milk glaze.

title: baked beans
directions: Layer beans in deep casserole dish, several layers like lasagna:
beans, bacon, onion, brown sugar, ketchup.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
The longer, the better.
Do not stir.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, celery and onion.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in reserved broth; debone chicken.
Saute pepper; add soups and Velveeta.
Put all items in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350° until heated through.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make salad ahead and chill overnight.
Leave out bacon, nuts and dressing untill ready to serve.
Dressing:
1 cup mayonnaise. 1/2 cup milk, 1 tsp. vinegar, 1/4 cup sugar.

title: ham salad
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in salted water in saucepan until tender-crisp; drain.
Mix olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper in bowl.
Add cauliflower.
Chill in refrigerator.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix lightly.
Slice avocado over salad. Yield:
6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together and put 1/2 of mixture aside. Add Minute rice to remaining 1/2 of soup mixture and stir well. Pour into oblong casserole dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice mixture.
I use 2 pieces of breasts and 2 thighs.
Pour rest of soup mixture over chicken.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: scripture cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter into sugar, add lightly beaten egg yolks.
Gradually mix the dry ingredients with the butter and egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stir in.
Add 1/2 cup water and balance of ingredients. Beat well and turn into 9-inch square pans, greased and floured. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: big game baked round steak(can use antelope, elk or moose)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim meat; cut into serving size pieces. Pound to 1/2-inch thickness with meat mallet.
On a sheet of waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip steaks in flour mixture, turning to coat.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Grease a 10 inch bundt pan. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 c pecan; set aside. Combine cake mix, oil, sugar, vanilla, eggs, and sour cream; beat for 2 minutes, at medium speed with an electric mixer. Stir in 1/2 c pecans. Pour 1/2 batter into prepared pan; sprinkle brown sugar mixture over batter. Pour remaining batter into pan. Bake at 325 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix well the powdered sugar, oleo, milk and peanut butter. Microwave on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Beat in vanilla.
Pour into a buttered pan and cool.

title: no-bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in heavy pan on top of stove until it comes to a rolling boil.
Take off stove; add salt, vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix good.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.
(You have to mix fast or it will get too hard to spoon on wax paper.)

title: lemon supreme
directions: Mix cake mix with oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add apricot nectar (I substitute orange juice if I can't find nectar).
Mix in Jell-O and flavoring.
Bake in cake tube or Bundt pan 45 minutes at 350°.
Cake must be cool to ice.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Top with raisins or sprinkle with colored sugar.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and place in a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch jellyroll pan, or other pan.
Press edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing mix; beat at medium speed with mixer for 1 minute.
Spread over crust in pan.
Combine pepper and remaining ingredients; sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Cover and chill for 8 hours, or overnight.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 8 dozen.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter in a saucepan. Stir until well blended.
In a large bowl, pour chocolate mixture over cereal until well coated.
Sift powdered sugar into a plastic storage bag; add the coated cereal and roll gently until all sugar is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over oyster soup crackers.
Mix well.
Let stand at least 1 hour.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain.
Beat egg with a small amount of milk. Dip cauliflower in egg mixture.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep hot oil until brown.

title: corn meal flat bread(flat brod)
directions: Pour boiling water over the corn meal and margarine and mix well.
Mixture should be consistency of thick soup.
Cover and let stand overnight.
The next day, add flour and salt to taste and mix well.
Form into small balls and roll out on floured pastry cloth, using cut lefse rolling pin.
Fry on hot lefse grill and turn once.
Makes 37 pieces.

title: all american apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for a filled 2-crust pie using a 9-inch pie plate.
Set aside.

title: london broil
directions: Buy thick cut, no marbling!
Place in Pyrex dish.
Stick fork in meat several places.
Sprinkle Season-All salt over meat. Cover meat with pats of oleo; put A.1. sauce and Worcestershire sauce over top.
Broil for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Turn meat, repeat steps starting with Season-All salt.
With electric knife, cut diagonally in thin slices; put back in pan with 2 cans mushroom gravy.
Cover meat with gravy.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pam's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, pineapple, green pepper and half of the nuts.
Shape into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.

title: nana's monkey bread
directions: Caramel Sauce:
Mix margarine and brown sugar.
Melt and mix again.

title: cheese ball
directions: Reserve 3 slices of beef to cover cheese ball.
Chop the rest into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients well and shape into a ball.
Cover with reserved beef.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; break into chunks.
Layer in casserole dish.
Bring soup, butter and chicken broth to a boil and pour over chicken.
At this time you may choose to add boiled eggs and a layer of egg noodles.
Stir together flour and milk and spoon over mixture (do not pour).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: les fraises au fondue de chocolate(strawberries with simple chocolate fondue dip)
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and chocolate on low-medium heat.
As chips begin to melt, add 1/4 cup milk, stir and add more milk if you want a thinner chocolate fondue.
Keep stirring until fondue is melted completely and even.
Remove from heat and dip strawberries while sauce is still warm.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut. Pat mixture lightly into ungreased oblong pan, building up slight edges.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg yolks; drizzle over apples.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until edges are light brown.
Serve warm.

title: strawberry stuff
directions: Always have filling hot when you add topping.

title: super bowl taco dip
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain grease.
Add taco seasoning. Spread in bottom of baking pan or casserole dish.
Spread sour cream on top of beef.
Sprinkle cheese on
top.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.
Serve with taco chips and salsa.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil; cook 2 minutes longer.
Add oats.
Add vanilla and pecans, if desired.
Last, add peanut butter and mix well.
Drop onto waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chili cheddar omelet(serves 2)
directions: In small bowl, beat eggs, water and seasoned salt together. Pour mixture into well-buttered 10-inch skillet.
Cook omelet over medium heat, letting liquid egg run to edges.
When eggs are set, slide omelet onto serving plate.
Place chili and grated cheese on half of omelet.
Fold over other half.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and salt; beat until lemon colored.
Add butter and flour; blend well.
Add milk and 1 cup coconut; pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining coconut.
Bake in 300° oven until slightly brown.
Reduce temperature to 275°; bake until done.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Combine chicken and 1/2 of the cheese. Separate the crescent rolls. Fill with chicken mixture. Roll up and place in ungreased pan.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown meat (drain) add other ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes (good and fast).
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling; add buttermilk.
Refrigerate one hour.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill until set.

title: yum yum cupcakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients together, then stir in dry ingredients.
Fill cupcake tins 1/2 full with chocolate mixture.
Top with about 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen cupcakes.

title: linguini salad
directions: Toss together cooked linguini, salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: 4 hour stew
directions: Oil casserole.
Place beef in bottom of pan; add vegetables, salt, sugar, tapioca and juice.
Stir well; cover and cook at 250° for 4 hours.
Do not stir while in oven.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Dredge steak in flour.
Brown well on both sides in hot oil. Place meat in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour off excess oil. Scrape up browned drippings left in pan and add to meat.
Arrange potatoes with meat.
Sprinkle onion, parsley, salt and pepper over all.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 10 minutes.
Cook frozen broccoli and drain.
Chop broccoli and place in casserole dish.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and place on top of broccoli.
In small saucepan, heat cream of chicken soup with sour cream.
When heated, add shredded cheese.
After cheese has blended with soup, pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with onion rings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn flake coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Gradually add sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Beat in salt.
Fold in corn flakes and coconut.
Drop mixture by teaspoon onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour into two 8 or 9-inch round pans. Bake as directed. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cool completely. Place cake layers, top side up, back in cleaned pans. Prick each with a utility fork at about 1/2-inch intervals. Pour 1 cup of the boiling water over the raspberry gelatin; stir until dissolved. Spoon over one layer. Repeat with lime gelatin over other layer. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours. Dip one layer in pan of hot water for 10 seconds; invert on serving plate. Spread with 1 cup Cool Whip. Repeat with remaining layer, inverting it onto the Cool Whip. Frost with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate. Garnish with flattened gumdrops out to resemble holly, if desired.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well; form into small balls (messy, gives you green hands).
Chill well.
May be frozen before baking.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Makes approximately 80 balls.

title: dutch toasts
directions: Finely chop the pickle.
Put the tomatoes into boiling water for 30 to 45 seconds.
Peel and cut into thick slices.
Mix chicken with pickle, parsley, oil, capers and mayonnaise.
Toast slices of bread.
Cover with tomato slices and then spoon on the chicken mixture.
Slice the cucumber very thinly and arrange on the chicken mixture.
Cover with a slice of cheese and place under a broiler until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and dice 2 medium eggplants in saucepan.
Cover with water; add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1 teaspoon sage.
Cook until tender, about 5 minutes, in baking pan.
Mix cornbread, 1 chopped onion, 1 sweet bell pepper and 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour eggplants and liquids over; stir to mix well.
Add 2 beaten eggs; stir again.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven 1/2 to 1 hour until cheese has melted well.

title: blue ribbon ham casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Add cheese and milk.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter on stove.
Remove from stove. Stir in sugar until smooth (I knead by hand).
Put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Keep in refrigerator or cupboard.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: brownie pudding cake
directions: Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt. Add milk, butter and vanilla, beat well. Stir in walnuts and food color. Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan.

title: marilyn's brownies
directions: Stir together the flour, sugar and cocoa. Add the oil and beat.
Add the eggs and beat.
Stir in the vanilla and nuts (optional).
Pour in greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add sour cream.
Set this gravy aside. In a 10 x 13-inch cake pan, lightly greased, layer the next 3 ingredients (2 or 3 layers).
Spread gravy on top of each layer. Top with sliced green onions and tomatoes for garnish.
Mild salsa may be used instead of tomatoes.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in a 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Cut steak in 1-inch squares, brown on all sides in tablespoon of fat.
Remove steak; mix water with gravy mix and add remaining ingredients; bring to boil; add steak.
Simmer covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf and serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly but well.
Add dry ingredients until blended.
Add raisins and nuts.
Put in 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: easy chocolate dessert
directions: Place crushed cookies in the bottom of a square container that can be sealed.
Spread softened ice cream on top of cookies.
Seal and freeze.
Before serving, ice with Cool Whip.
Dribble with chocolate syrup and garnish with walnuts/pecans and cherries.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Mix all ingredients and pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese last 5 minutes.

title: sabra pie
directions: Mix gingersnaps crumbs and butter together.
Press into 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Marinate in 1/2 cup oil, 1/2 cup vinegar and 1/2 cup vinegar. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mrs. harvey's white fruitcake
directions: Chop nuts and fruits into medium sized pieces.
Dredge with small amount of flour (about 1/4 cup).

title: sweet potato souffle #1
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart greased baking dish.
Spread Topping over souffle.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until topping starts to brown.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Drain and cut sauerkraut.
Brown onion lightly in butter.
Add ham and brown.
Add garlic and flour; stir in bouillon, sauerkraut and parsley.
Cook until thick.
Spread in pan and chill for 2 hours.
Make into walnut size balls.
Dip in flour; then in mixture of egg and milk beaten together.
Roll in bread crumbs and deep fry.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 50.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In large pan, combine beef and onion.
Cook until onion is translucent.
Add remainder of ingredients-except tortilla shells.
Simmer until done.
Cut or tear 3 or 4 tortilla shells into small pieces and drop into simmering soup for last 5 minutes of cooking. You may have to add some water during cooking.
This makes a Big Pot of Soup.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onions in small amount of salted water; drain.
Break salmon into chunks.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add carrots, onions and macaroni.
Stir in soup, salt and pepper.
Melt butter.
Toss with bread crumbs.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven for about 20 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: Place milk in large pot on stove and bring to a simmer. Add butter, salt and pepper to taste. When butter is melted, add oysters and allow to simmer 10 or 15 minutes. Serve with oyster crackers.

title: lamb with green beans
directions: Brown lamb chops.
Add water mixed with tomato sauce.
Cook about 30 minutes, then add green beans, onion, potatoes and salt and pepper.
Add more water and tomato sauce, if needed.
Cover and cook one hour or until done to your preference.
Serves 2. May be doubled.

title: fast food biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and Crisco. Cut mixture until it resembles cornmeal. Add buttermilk and stir until the dough does not stick to sides of bowl. Turn out on floured surface and roll dough for 5 minutes. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on a greased baking pan. Coat with melted butter. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: batter fried shrimp
directions: In small bowl, mix flour, beer and salt.
Shell and devein shrimp; rinse with running cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat 2 inches of salad oil to 375° on deep fat thermometer (or heat oil in deep fat fryer set at 375°).
Dip shrimp, one at a time, into batter and drop into hot oil.
Fry shrimp until lightly browned, turning shrimp once, about 1 minute.
Drain shrimp on paper towels. Serves 6.

title: essie's mix
directions: Add all ingredients together starting with 2 cups each. Add more if you wish. A very good snack.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together the shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar; cream well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls (about 1 rounded teaspoonful).
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes; remove from oven and place solid chocolate candy kiss on top of each cookie, pressing down so cookie cracks around edge.
Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.
Cool.

title: snicker apples
directions: Cut up apples, quarters or smaller.
Stir in Cool Whip to Snickers.
Chill until time to serve.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix together corn meal, sugar, and scald with boiling water. Beat eggs and add milk.
Combine the above and add baking powder. Pour mixture into baking pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix everything except nuts and parsley.
Roll in the mixture then refrigerate.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Crumble corned beef into
a
bowl;
add cottage cheese, scallions, peppers, parsley
and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill several hours to blend flavors and to firm mixture. (It can be left overnight in fridge.)
Remove mixture from bowl and shape into a ball.
Spread cream
cheese
evenly over ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to be used.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon and remove (retaining grease). Thicken grease with flour.
Add vinegar and enough water so it's not really thick.
Mix potatoes, bacon and onions.
Pour topping over potato mixture "like gravy."

title: chicken and spinach bake
directions: Defrost spinach and drain well. Distribute spinach evenly on the bottom of a rectangular baking dish.
Pour chicken broth over spinach, then sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Dip chicken cutlets into flour.
Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter and the 2 tablespoons of margarine and fry the chicken cutlets until light brown.
Place the cutlets on top of the spinach.
Place a slice of ham and Swiss cheese on top of each cutlet.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all and dot with remaining 1 1/2 tablespoons butter. Cover and bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch oaties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butterscotch morsels and butter.
Melt over boiling water.
Remove from heat.

title: no bake cocoa haystacks
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, oats, coconut and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Store in a cool dry place.
Makes about 4 dozen candies.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: In blender, blend eggs, oil, pepper and cheese.
Add Bisquick. Add to vegetables.
Pour into a 9-inch greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; mix in remaining ingredients.
(Make sure vegetables are dry before adding to potatoes.)
Let chill overnight.

title: daddy's chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Dip chicken in buttermilk, then in bread crumb mixture. Fry in hot skillet with a little Crisco. Put on cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes until done.

title: steak house french dressing
directions: Put into blender and blend well.
Put into container and refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put in 2 small Pet pie crusts. Bake at 300° until real brown.

title: chesapeake crab meat moray
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan; saute onions and parsley. Blend in flour.
Slowly add cream; heat.
Stir until thick.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add sherry, red peppers (if used) and salt; gently fold in crab meat.
Let chill for 2 hours or overnight.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and mayonnaise together. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet. May be topped with walnuts or pecan halves. Bake until edges are golden at 350°.

title: cherry cheese pie 2(leanna cerbu)
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in milk until smooth. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla, then pour whole mixture into graham cracker crust. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk, salt, butter and chocolate.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoonful on wax paper or brown paper bag.

title: beef burgundy
directions: In large heavy pan, brown beef in oil; pour off fat.
Add soup, water and Burgundy.
Cover; cook over low heat for 2 hours. Add noodles and mushrooms.
Cook 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Add more water if necessary.

title: chicken wings paella(brave's rafael belliard recipe)
directions: In an 8-quart Dutch oven, cook the chicken wings and sausages until browned on all sides and cooked through, about 25 minutes. Remove to a large bowl.
Remove all but 2 or 3 tablespoons of the drippings in the Dutch oven and cook the onions, red pepper and zucchini until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes with liquid, water, orzo, salt, oregano, paprika, turmeric, pepper sauce and browned wings and sausage.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until orzo is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.

title: potato cheese patties
directions: In
a bowl, mix potatoes, egg and diced American cheese slices with potato masher until blended well.
Spoon into hot grease; turn when browned.
Serve as side dish.

title: bowknots(fattigmann)
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick (lemon colored).
Add sugar.
Stir in butter.
Fold in whipped cream and cardamon.
Sift flour and salt.
Fold into yolk mixture to make soft dough.
Chill.
Divide in half.
Roll each piece on lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut 3 x 3/4-inch strips.
Cut slit lengthwise in center of each and pull one end through.
Fry few at a time in deep hot fat at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until light golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
While warm, sift a little confectioners sugar over.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook pasta or noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Combine mayonnaise with milk or white wine.
Stir in soup, cheese and seasonings.
Gently stir in cooked pasta or noodles and drained fish or seafood.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with "Crunchy Topping." Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french bread roll-up
directions: Unroll the bread dough until you have a rectangle.

Brush on mustard allowing a 1 inch border of plain dough on all four sides. Layer the meat and cheese on the dough up to the plain border. Start at one end and roll-up like a jelly roll, placing the seam side down.
With fork prick four or five times along the top to create steam vents.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine dry ingredients, set aside.
Combine wet ingredients and add to dry.
Do not overmix.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
These are wonderful, moist brownies.

title: chocolate zucchini loaf
directions: In small heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Or, in small glass bowl, microwave chocolate on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute.

title: chicken-pasta primavera
directions: Cook vegetables in oil.
Stir in chicken, salt and tomatoes; heat.
Spoon over pasta.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in Crisco until crumbly.
Add liquid mixture.
Mix until all is moistened.
Great for pasties.

title: champagne cocktail
directions: Take 2 heaping cups patience, 1 heartful of love, 2 handfuls of generosity, plenty of laughter, 1 headful of understanding and sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith; mix well. Spread over a period of a lifetime and serve everybody with a smile whomever you meet.

title: company creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; drain well.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Place in 1 1/2-quart to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir.
Top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: tomato vegetable soup
directions: Mix together.
Heat and serve with your favorite crackers.

title: brownies
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt butter and cocoa together.
Mix all ingredients, adding eggs one at a time and beating well after each egg.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pullet surprise
directions: Rub the chicken pieces with seasonings, then brown in margarine.
Put in a shallow dish with the mushrooms and drained artichokes.
Mix the soup, sour cream and wine with the chicken drippings and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Garnish with the parsley.

title: sandra's cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and cream cheese; gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla; gradually add flour and whipped topping mix.
Stir well.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.
May be glazed, if desired.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add water and rest of ingredients. Heat to boiling.
Lower heat and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour until vegetables are tender.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake cookies 15 to 20 minutes at 300°.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Dissolve Jell-O according to directions on package.
Set aside to cool.
Add strawberries and Cool Whip.
Combine cold milk, pudding mix and sour cream.
Layer dish with vanilla wafers, pudding mixture and strawberry mixture, repeating until dish is full.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: basic marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place meat in large plastic bag. Put bag in bowl and pour marinade over meat in bag.
Tie bag closed.
Marinate meat several hours or overnight.
Brush marinade on during grilling also.

title: swiss string beans
directions: Combine and cook the butter, flour, sour cream, grated onion, salt, pepper and sugar until thick.
Mixture does not get real thick.
Cook the two packages of string beans and drain well.
In greased casserole, combine green beans and white sauce.
Spread Swiss cheese on top of mixture.
Combine crushed corn flakes with 2 tablespoons of butter and sprinkle on top of string beans mixture and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: lemon dijon baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut fillets in half. Arrange in lightly greased pan. Mix together mustard, butter, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Spread mixture over fillets.
Crush crackers finely and sprinkle on fish. Bake 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: mattie's tea cakes
directions: Work all this together with enough self-rising flour to make a stiff dough.
Roll this out and cut out cookies and bake on buttered baking sheet.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Put first 6 ingredients in a blender and mix.
Add ice until thick.

title: sui mai
directions: Mix ingredients for the filling.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons on the center of each won ton skin. Gather upward and pinch lightly where all edges meet over the filling, leaving the top of the Sui Mai open and the edges to ruffle freely.
Steam for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a greased dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole green beans
directions: Cook onion in salad oil until soft. Add chili sauce, salt and drained beans. Cook only until thoroughly heated, stirring often. Serves 6.

title: monkey bread
directions: At 10:00 p.m. or 8 hours before serving:
place nuts in angel food cake pan.
Place 20 frozen rolls in pan and pour pudding mix over rolls.
Melt margarine and pour over.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cover and let set overnight or until raised up out of pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then invert onto cake plate and pull apart.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(red lobster)
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, cheese, parsley and pepper to form a soft dough.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 450° oven until golden brown.
Mix butter and garlic powder; pour over warm biscuits on cookie sheet.
Serve warm!
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: texas style chili
directions: In large kettle or Dutch oven, brown meat (if using beef, pour off fat).
Add onion, pepper and garlic; cook and stir until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 hours (1 hour for ground beef) or until meat is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve with corn chips and sweet pepper salsa.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Place crackers in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and eggs together.
Add salt and pepper; pour over onions.
Cover with cheese and bake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter, press into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° unti light brown (approximately 15 minutes).
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add sliced strawberries over top of white mixture.
(May use strawberry glaze if desired.) Refrigerate.
Cool, then slice and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread and mix all ingredients together.
Add a boiled egg if you wish.

title: low country boil
directions: Add 6 ounces of Old Savannah to one gallon of water and bring to a boil.
Add 16 half ears of corn and boil for 7 minutes.
Then add 3 pounds smoked sausage and boil for 3 minutes.
Add 3 pounds of shrimp and boil for 3 minutes.
Drain and serve with butter and cocktail sauce.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers (sliced), onions (sliced) and sliced red and green peppers in gallon or 1/2 gallon jars.
Boil the vinegar, sugar and spices with small amount of water.
Let come to a hard boil and pour over vegetables.
Cover jar and refrigerate.
Keeps for months in refrigerator.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Mix well; drizzle over chocolate and nuts.

title: tomato rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Add chicken broth, tomato and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and olives. Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: sticky wings
directions: Wash and pat dry wings.
Mix all ingredients together and marinate wings in mixture for several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.

title: irresistable brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips and nuts (if desired).
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of chocolate chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until set.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut into 2 inch squares.

title: baked dish
directions: Mix together.
Bake with fine bread crumbs on top for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with corn and cabbage cole slaw.

title: grandma's treasured cheesecake
directions: Mix and pour over crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake 1 hour.
Let cool.
Loosen pan.

title: quick relish
directions: Slice onion paper thin.
Place in small saucepan and add vinegar, sugar, mustard and seasoning.
Cook 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Stir in corn.
Cool.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: winning corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish (spray with nonstick vegetable coating) and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: baked brie
directions: Spread thawed pastry sheet on baking sheet.
Place Brie (or Camembert) in center of sheet.
(Optional:
Remove rind from cheese prior to placing on pastry sheet.)
Spread honey mustard or apricot preserves on top of cheese.
(If honey mustard is used, sprinkle a small amount of brown sugar on top.)
Wrap cheese in pastry; bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour and other dry ingredients into separate bowl.
Stir together; blend in.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately browned. (Cookies should still be soft, cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.)
Makes 8 to 9 dozen.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add grated zucchini and stir well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add nuts and add to zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: pizza
directions: Combine flour, yeast and salt.
In a 1-cup measuring cup, combine water, oil and honey. Stir into flour mixture.
Knead and place into a well-greased glass bowl.
Let rise in warm place, covered, until double (2 hours).
Roll out to size of 14-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle pan with cornmeal.
Place dough and roll edges. Top with 1 cup spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese and favorite toppings.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. If desired, lightly brush edge of crust with oil before baking.

title: cinnamon ornaments(no baking and simple for kids.)
directions: Combine.
Roll out dough to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole for ribbon (a nail works well for this).
Carefully place on wire rack to dry.
Let air dry several days (turning occasionally).
Makes 12 sweet smelling ornaments.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, butter and milk.
Boil 12 minutes, then add the marshmallow, chocolate chips, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts (if desired).

title: brown bread
directions: Simmer raisins in water (covered 50 to 60 minutes).
Mix flour, sugar, salt, margarine, egg and baking soda.
Then add raisins and any water left in pan.
Be sure to add a little water if needed.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: missy's chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Melt oleo.
Add lemon juice and onions.
Steam chicken until done.
Place chicken breast on plate and pour sauce over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli
directions: Mix top three ingredients, then bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Add cheese and onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Dip balls into chocolate mixture with fork and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate until set.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: three step cheesecake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip(nacho or corn chips)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve warm.
Can use as dip or pour over platter of chips and heat a can of Armour chili with beans and pour over top of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with fresh parsley, red pepper, chili peppers and/or sour cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all, except cheese, nuts and potato chips.
If salad appears too dry, add 1/2 cup of chicken broth.

title: pimento cheese(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Mix and spread for sandwiches.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small bowl mix eggs, milk and butter; stir and add to flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Pour batter on preheated waffle iron (lightly greased).
Makes approximately 12 waffles.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix well by hand the first four ingredients.
Pat into two 8 x 8 pans lined with foil.
Melt chocolate chips and spread thinly over top of the above.
Score squares with knife before refrigerating.
When cool cut into squares and serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil water and sugar together 10 minutes. Add strong tea, cherries, strawberry syrup and lemon and orange juices.
Stir in crushed pineapple and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add ice water and ginger ale. Serves 50.

title: pecan coffee cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine pecans, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter. Cut through with a knife to swirl. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: basic flan recipe
directions: Beat butter, sugar and yolks until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients, add alternately with flavoring and milk.
Blend well. Pour into greased and floured flan pan.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture is reduced slightly and thickened, about 15 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Cook, stirring constantly until melted and thoroughly combined.
Sprinkle with baking soda and stir until dissolved.
Mixture will puff.
Pour onto cutting board and let cool.
Use rolling pin and roll into a 6-inch square.
Cut into 4 pieces.
Cool on wire rack. Crack into smaller pieces when hard.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in small saucepan. Boil 1 minute after it comes to a boil.
Remove from stove and stir in oatmeal, pecans and vanilla.
Mix well until all oatmeal is coated.
Drop by the teaspoonful on waxed paper or foil.
Let cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except artichokes.
Add artichokes and mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: seafood sauce picante
directions: Brown sausage.
Add tomatoes, onions and bell peppers.
Cook until thick.
Add 3 cups of water (more if needed), salt and pepper.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and crabmeat; cook another 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: raisin nut banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of loaf pan. Stir together cereal and milk. Let stand about 5 minutes or until cereal is softened. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into loaf pan. Bake until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes. Loosen sides of loaf from pan. Place upside down on wire rack. Cool completely before slicing. Wrap tightly and store at room temperature.

title: green chile casserole
directions: Grate cheese.
Layer cheese and chilies in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Beat egg whites stiff.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks.
Add flour, then gradually add milk.
Fold in egg whites and pour over cheese and chilies.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: tomato pie
directions: Place tomato slices in colander, salt to taste, and drain for 10 minutes. Place tomato slices, basil, and onions in baked pie shell. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, and garlic powder to taste. Mix mayo

and cheese together in a bowl. Spread on top of tomato mixture, like a meringue. bake 45 minutes at 350 degrees. Serve warm, can be reheated as individual slices in microwave for about 15 seconds. This is sort of like a quiche.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine 1/2 can onions and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir and top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: pork and noodle casserole
directions: Fry pork, onions and green pepper in skillet.
Boil noodles until tender.
Add to skillet, along with tomato paste and water. Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice cheese on top and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Ingredients may be transferred to baking dish before baking, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: quiche with hash browns
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate with 1/3 cup melted butter.
Press thawed hash browns into butter.
Brush butter over tops of hash browns.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Remove.
Fill with cheese and ham and onions.
Beat eggs and salt and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake until knife comes out of center clean.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Press dough into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate morsels.
Let stand 5 minutes or until morsels melt; spread evenly over surface.
Combine powdered sugar, 1/4 cup peanut butter and milk in a small mixing bowl; beat well.
Drizzle mixture over cookies.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Yield:
About 4 1/2 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar together: add Cool Whip.
Mix pudding and milk in separate bowl, mix pudding mixture with cream cheese mixture.
Crush Oreo cookies in large bowl.
Layer cookies then layer of filling until entire amount of mixture and cookies have been used.

title: crunchy slaw
directions: Combine mayonnaise, soy sauce, sugar and salt in a large bowl and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well.

title: joan's chocolate fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and put in heavy pan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Set off stove.
Add Marshmallow Creme, chocolate bits and nuts.
Stir until thick and then pour in slightly greased cookie sheet until cool.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine ingredients together and put in a baking dish. Sprinkle almond slivers on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cool to lukewarm.
Stir next
2 ingredients together to dissolve; add to first mixture.
Beat egg whites and add to first mixture.
Add half the flour and beat well.
Stir in enough more to make dough easy to handle.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine the
two
soups,
rice and water in 9 x 13-inch dish. Place
chicken
breasts
on top, meat side down.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in
a double boiler until thick. Then pour into a baked pie crust. Cover with meringue, then brown.

title: topping for ice cream
directions: Boil 3 minutes, stirring.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 large can evaporated milk.
Beat until well mixed.
This keeps a long time in the refrigerator.
Serve on warm cake, ice cream or puddings.

title: salmon with cilantro salsa
directions: Lay fillets, skin side down, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Evenly drizzle 2 tablespoons of lime juice over the fillets.
In a small bowl, combine remaining lime juice, onions, jalapenos, cilantro and olive oil; spread 1/2 cup of the cilantro salsa over 1 fillet.
Lay
the other fillet, skin side up, atop the first, fitting together neatly.
If made ahead, cover and chill salmon up to overnight.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Combine water, oil, and honey.
Add yeast, and salt.
Mix. Add all other dry ingredients.
Mix until dough clears side of mixing bowl.
Let dough rise until double.
Divide into 2 loaves and place into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
Butter top of loaves if desired.

title: uncooked chocolate butter frosting
directions: Cream the margarine.
Gradually add half of the sugar.
Beat in the egg.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar. If needed, add a little milk to make of spreading consistency. Frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, sour milk, butter, shortening, vanilla and bananas.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan or 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn to 300° and bake about 1 hour.

title: wedding punch
directions: Place orange sherbet in punch bowl.
Tear into small pieces. Pour ginger ale over sherbet and stir gently.

title: pie crust
directions: Dump into pie pan; push around, do not prick.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter.
Combine crackers, breadcrumbs, Parmesan, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Wash and dry chicken breasts. Coat chicken well with butter and roll in crumbs (sprinkle any remaining butter and crumbs on top).
Arrange in a lightly greased baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
(You may sprinkle fresh grated Parmesan over the top during the last 10 minutes.)
Serves 4.

title: pasta pizza
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
For pasta crust, in a large bowl, combine egg, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in pasta.
Spread pasta mixture evenly in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
In large skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Add pepper, undrained tomatoes and Italian seasoning.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 10 to 12 minutes until most of liquid evaporates.
Stir in mushrooms.
Spoon meat mixture over pasta crust.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dice the veggies while you cook the noodles.
Rinse and cool. Add veggies, mayo, salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage (not as fine as for slaw).
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes in oleo.
Let cabbage set in cold water 3 minutes.
Mix celery soup, milk and mayonnaise together. Pour cabbage in on corn flakes.
Pour mixture of soup, milk and mayonnaise over cabbage.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese and some corn flakes over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: harlequin ham casserole
directions: Cook rice, salt and water until rice is done.
Make a cream sauce of the flour, margarine, milk, mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350° and grease an 8-inch square pan. Blend together shortening, peanut butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and fold in coconut.
Place in prepared pan and bake 30 minutes.
While still warm, cut and roll each square in sifted confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 squares.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Blot sausage dry with paper towel and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper. Lightly grease muffin pan (small or large size) and press 1 wrapper in each cup (if using egg roll wrappers, press 2 crossways).
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden. Remove from tins; place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen. Delicious!

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients; baste to chicken.

title: peanut butter crumb pie
directions: Place powdered sugar and peanut butter in small bowl.
Cut with pastry cutter until it resembles crumbs (size of very small peas).
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture in bottom of pie crust; reserve the rest for later.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box; pour over crumbs in crust.
Cover top with thawed Cool Whip. Cover Cool Whip with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: sunbelt strawberry bread(yields two 9 x 5-inch loaves)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
In large mixing bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
Blend oil and eggs into strawberries; add to flour mixture.
Blend until dry ingredients are just moistened. Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool in pans on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; let cool completely on wire racks.

title: baked chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Add chicken and noodles. Pour into 1-quart dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Stew chicken in salted water until done.
Bone; cut into small pieces.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Put layer of broccoli in buttered casserole, then layer of chicken.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper and pour over.
Cover with grated cheese, then buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: ham and corn chowder
directions: Mix all; heat slowly.
Make day before.

title: cheeseburger soup
directions: In a
large
pot place the first 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Fry the hamburger; drain.
Add to the ingredients in the large pot, along with the remaining ingredients. Simmer until cheese melts.

title: double chocolate swirl bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray loaf pan (I use a pan that makes 4 mini loaves) with nonstick cooking spray.
Coarsely chop almonds and half of the white chocolate morsels; place in bowl and set aside.
On lightly floured surface, unroll 1 package of bread dough.
Don't stretch.

Lightly beat egg white and water in small bowl; brush dough with a portion of the egg mixture. Grate half of the semi-sweet chocolate morsels evenly over dough. Sprinkle with half of the almond and white chocolate mixture; roll lightly with rolling pin, pressing mixture into dough.
Unroll remaining package of bread dough directly over first dough layer, matching seams and rolling lightly to seal.
Brush dough lightly with a portion of the egg mixture; grate remaining chocolate morsels over dough and sprinkle with remaining white chocolate and almond mixture.
Roll lightly with rolling pin.
Starting at narrow edge, roll dough up tightly; press edge to seal.
Slice roll into 4 equal portions; place seam side down in pan.
Make deep cut down the length of each loaf without cutting through ends.
Brush loaves with remaining egg mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown (center of loaves may appear moist). Cool for 5 minutes.
Remove loaves from pan.
Cool completely. Microwave remaining white chocolate and oil, uncovered on high for 30 to 40 seconds or until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Do not over heat.
Drizzle chocolate over loaves; sprinkle with sliced almonds or chocolate morsels.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses and mayonnaise well together.
Then add ham, then pimentos (optional).
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: sweet and sour chicken packets
directions: In small bowl, combine reserved pineapple juice, cornstarch, sugar, soy sauce, bouillon and ginger and mix well.
On each of 4 large squares of aluminum foil, place a chicken breast, equal amounts of fruit, vegetables and sauce mixture.
Fold and seal foil around chicken.
Place packets on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: fiesta crepes en casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; beat until smooth.
For each crepe, pour 1/4 cup batter into hot, lightly greased crepe pan or small skillet; tilt pan to coat bottom evenly.
Cook over medium heat until top is dull and underside is delicately browned.
Turn, cook another 10 to 15 seconds.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix crushed pineapple, juice and all with the pudding mix and allow to set until it thickens.
Fold in the marshmallows and Cool Whip and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients together. Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Cut off wing tips and cut wings into 2 pieces.
Marinate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn each wing piece and bake another 20 minutes or until tender and slightly crisp.

title: thousand dollar salad
directions: Dissolve orange gelatin in boiling water in large bowl.
Stir in 7-Up.
Chill for 45 minutes.
Add next 5 ingredients; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into serving container and chill.

title: basic guacamole
directions: Omit salt and Worcestershire sauce; add 1 envelope onion soup mix and 1/2 cup dairy sour cream.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add frozen berries (do not thaw), pineapple and bananas.
Stir to mix.
Pour half the mixture into 12 x 7-inch pan; refrigerate to set.
Spread half of sour cream over and pour the other half of mixture on top of sour cream.
Spread remaining sour cream on top when jelled.
(Or use all of the sour cream in the center.)
Serve in squares.

title: baked chicken breast supreme
directions: In large bowl combine first seven ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Remove chicken from marinate and coat each piece with bread crumbs.
Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Skin and bone chicken breasts and pound to about 1/4-inch thickness.
In a small bowl, combine melted butter and Dijon mustard.
In a separate dish, combine bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Completely coat each chicken breast in mustard mixture and then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: add about anything cookies
directions: Beat the ingredients together.
Add 3 cups of anything.
Drop teaspoon of batter on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 80 cookies.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with water and lime.
Soak for 24 hours. Rinse well with clear water.
Soak in clear water for 3 hours, or more.
Drain.

title: parmesan mashed potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes with the skin on.
Cook potatoes in water, adding oregano, chives and chopped onions.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Drain water.
Add Parmesan cheese and butter.
Mash potatoes, adding sour cream to the consistency you prefer.
Salt to taste.
Sprinkle bacon bits over the potatoes and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add vanilla;
mix well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.

title: french fried onions
directions: Slice onions 1/8-inch thick, using only large middle slices. Separate rings and cover with ice water (about 1 tablespoon of sugar to a bowl of ice water).
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain and wipe dry.
Combine flour, salt and the 2/3 cup water.
Add oil and fold in beaten egg whites.
Dip each onion ring in the batter and fry in deep, hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with salt.

title: polish sausage stew
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and simmer carrots until tender, usually 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable-tortellini soup
directions: Combine water, bouillon granules, basil and oregano in a medium saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in carrots and tortellini.

title: rolled stuffed steak
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in 4 tablespoons butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing mix, egg, jalapeno pepper, oregano and water.
Mix well.
Spread sandwich steak on a board, spread stuffing over steak; roll up jelly roll style, tucking ends in.
Secure with skewers, toothpicks or tie with string.
Heat the remaining butter in a skillet.
Brown rolled steak slowly and evenly all over.
Pour in beef broth and cover.
Simmer 1 hour.
Remove meat to a serving plate while making gravy.
Make a smooth paste with the flour and about 3 tablespoons cold water; add to juices in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until gravy thickens and bubbles, about 3 minutes.
Spoon gravy over rolled steak and serve.

title: popcorn balls(childrens delight)
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water, salt and margarine in small sauce pan and cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves and mixture boils. Continue cooking without stirring until it reaches 250° on candy thermometer, hard ball stage. remove from heat and add vanilla. Pour slowly over popped corn in large bowl and mix to coat all kernels. Work quickly and shape into 4 inch balls. As you are working with part of corn, you can keep remaining in oven at 200° to stay warm and pliable. Place square of waxed paper under each ball.
