title: hot ham dip
directions: Mix ham, onion, pepper and mayonnaise.
Pour in small baking dish.
Heat at 400° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture and bake a few minutes until cheese is melted (not browned).
It's best to use a small hard knife to spread mixture.
Serve with crackers and party rye bread.

title: peach crunch
directions: Pour cake mix in cake pan.
Pour peaches over cake mix.
Place butter slices all over top.
Bake until done.

title: three fruit punch
directions: Put fruit in a blender; blend until smooth.
Combine with ginger ale in punch bowl when ready to serve.

title: pumpkin layer cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer. Add eggs. Mix until blended. Stir pumpkin and spices into 1 cup of batter. Pour remaining plain batter into crust. Top with pumpkin batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil noodles.
Cut onion into small strips lengthways.
Cut cabbage, all strips lengthways.
Fry onion and cabbage until done. Add noodles, butter and garlic.
Fry and stir until light brown. Serve.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix margarine and garlic in small mixing bowl.
Cut bread horizontally on cutting board.
Spread top and bottom of bread with garlic margarine.

title: football pudding
directions: Measure ingredients according to package directions and place in large Ziploc bag.
Then put bag in another Ziploc bag.
Throw around until mixed.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together and set aside.
Mix cream cheese and egg yolks together.
Add to milk and lemon juice.
Fold in 2 cups of strawberries.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Chop onions and cook in fat.
Chop hamburg and add to onions and brown.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Boil until water from tomatoes evaporates, then add enough water to make soupy.
Cook until thickened over low heat.
Takes about 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend sugar, eggs and oil.
Mix all ingredients together until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for at least an hour.

title: bodacious bulgar
directions: Saute garlic, onions, peppers and bulgar in oil until onions are soft and bulgar is coated with oil.
Add spices, tomatoes and beans.
Cover and bring to a low boil.
Simmer 15 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and bulgar is tender.

title: baked chicken with tarragon sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Arrange in dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Chill 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Put mixture into floured and greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jezebel ham
directions: Score ham.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat, stirring until smooth.
Coat ham generously with sauce.
Bake at 350° until glazed.
Serve remaining sauce with sliced ham.

title: wedding punch
directions: Cut thin horizontal slice from bottom of watermelon so it will rest evenly.
Slice watermelon lengthwise in half.
Carve a decorative zigzag edge from sliced edge of 1/2 of watermelon. Scoop out fruit to form a bowl.
Scoop melon balls from second half.

title: venison tulips
directions: Cut venison into 1/3-inch strips, about 6 to 7-inches long, an inch or so wide.

title: farmer's supper
directions: Brown sausage with onions.
Drain off grease and spread on bottom of casserole.
Drain sauerkraut
and spread on top of sausage.
Mix shredded cheese with mashed potatoes and spread on top of sauerkraut.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler; stir and blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add hot milk all at once, stirring occasionally until smoothly thickened.

Remove from heat. Stir in yolks, parsley, onion, salmon and mayonnaise. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and turn into buttered 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° to 375° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Double this for a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: summer italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cold water to cool quickly; drain well. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Refrigerate several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Preparation time: 25 minutes plus refrigerating.

title: dirt and sand cups
directions: You also need 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups. Suggested garnishes: Gummy worms or other gummy candies, candy flowers, chopped peanuts or granola.

title: teen mix
directions: Cook bacon and onion. Add hamburger and cook until brown. Add remainder of ingredients. Cover and simmer over low heat for 20 minutes. Stir. Serve on a hamburger bun.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef with 1 teaspoon onion flakes.
Drain grease and set aside.
In crock-pot, add tomato paste, sauce, mushrooms, all remaining seasonings, including other teaspoon of onion flakes.
Cook on low at least 2 hours.
The longer cooked, the better it is.

title: condensed milk
directions: Put in shaker; shake to mix.
Chill.
May be used in recipes calling for Eagle Brand milk.

title: seafood salad
directions: Break tuna into chunks and add shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add eggs, celery, onions and capers.
Chill.
Lightly toss with mayonnaise and salt and pepper to taste.
Serve in lettuce cup.
Tuck in cucumber slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: weight watcher's best lasagna in the world
directions: In a large pan, brown beef, onion and seasonings.
Stir in tomato sauce, paste, mushrooms and water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
The mixture will be thin.
Mix together cottage, Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer 1/3 uncooked noodles, 1/3 cheese mixture, 1/3 sauce and 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with 2 more layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: indiana picnic cake
directions: Makes a thin batter.
Before baking, sprinkle with 1 cup reserved mixture.
Bake in greased and lightly floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
Very good picnic cake.

title: balsamic chicken with grapes & almonds
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in large non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; saute 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove chicken from the pan.
Reduce heat, stir in grapes, broth, vinegar and sugar. Bring to boil, cook until reduced to 1 c. (about 6 minutes). Return chicken to pan, cook 3 minutes or until done, turning to coat.
Sprinkle with almonds immediately before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage sandwiches
directions: Brown ground chuck and sausage.
Drain.
Add cheese, fennel and oregano.
Mix together and spoon onto rye bread squares.
Place on cookie sheet and heat at 375° until bubbly.
(These can be frozen until ready to use!)

title: sugar free lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Add milk, beating with a wire whisk until thickened; gently fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mixture evenly into crusts.
Garnish with lemon rind, if desired.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or freeze at least 8 hours.
Yields 16 servings.
This recipe makes two pies.
Chill one, and freeze the other one for later.

title: fig preserves
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O with sugar.
Add figs and bring to a boil.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Be sure to use new lids.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix carrots, macaroni, grated cheese, egg and salt.
Put in shallow pan or casserole dish.
Dot with butter and pour the milk over all the ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: italian meat sauce for pasta
directions: Heat olive oil in deep skillet, add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook until onion pieces are soft.
Add ground meat and cook until no longer pink.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients, except mushrooms, and let simmer, uncovered, for one hour.
During the last 15 minutes of cooking time, add mushrooms and adjust seasoning.
Serve immediately over cooked spaghetti. Top with grated cheese.
Serves 8.

title: english trifle
directions: Cut 1/2 the pound cake into slices and place in a large, deep glass dish.
Pour 1/2 cup of Amaretto on top of pound cake, then pour 1 packet of Jell-O on pound cake.
Add 1/2 can of mixed fruit, then chill for 1/2 hour.
Add remaining pound cake, second packet of Jell-O, remaining mixed fruit, and add pudding on the top.
Cover with Jimmies.
Chill for 1 hour, then ready to serve. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add to sugar, vinegar and sauce.
Set aside to cool.
Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Pour jello mixture into this.
Add other ingredients.
Let set.

title: eight treasure vegs
directions: In wok, stir shrimp in oil.
Add peanuts and vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve on rice.
Garnish with cucumber slices.

title: easy caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, butter and 1/2 cup cream. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add remaining 1/2 cup cream and cook to 240°. Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Cool and cut into squares.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dressing mix and spices. Pour over 2 packages of crackers and toss to coat. Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: smoked salmon party dip
directions: Put cottage cheese in a food processor or blender. Puree for 30 seconds or until smooth. Scrape into a medium bowl.
Stir in remaining dip ingredients. Cover and refrigerate.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into patties and fry until golden brown.

title: cabbage-fruit salad
directions: Combine cabbage, celery, apple and washed stemmed grapes. Toss lightly with the mayo.
Heap lightly on lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: curry chicken
directions: In frying pan, heat oil, green pepper, onion, garlic, curry powder, parsley, thyme, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Add chicken and put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: butter brickle dessert
directions: Crush crackers into crumbs and add melted margarine; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Beat egg; stir in milk and oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients, just until flour is moistened.
Should be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: english muffin snacks
directions: Mix well.
Spread on English muffin halves; put under broiler to lightly brown.
Cut in halves or quarter and serve.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: In soup pot, melt butter.
Add onion and saute until tender. Stir in flour (it will be quite thick).
Gradually add milk and stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
In a separate pot, cook broccoli in 3 cups water until tender.
Pour broccoli and water into soup pot with milk mixture.
Add everything else, except cheese.
Stir constantly over medium heat until thickened.
Turn heat to low and add Velveeta.
Stir until blended.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and place in oven to melt.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine together.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, beaten eggs and powdered sugar together and pour over unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: honey batter rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast and salt in mixer bowl. Add water, melted Crisco, honey and egg. Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add remaining cup flour. Beat with fork or spoon. Cover with plastic. Let rise 30 minutes or until double. Spoon into greased muffin tins (1/2 full). Cover; let rise until double. Preheat oven to 400°. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: eggs lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Brown sausage and drain well. Layer 1 cup of cheese in bottom of pan; top with eggs. Break yolks with fork; sprinkle with bell peppers, mushrooms and onions. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add sausage and pour cream over all. DO NOT MIX. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake for 1 hour or until set. Can be made the night before and refrigerated. Assemble without the cream. Pour cream over pan just before baking. Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until set.

title: the ultimate cheesecake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and sugar. Add melted butter; stir to combine.
Press crumb mixture into a 9 inch spring form pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: loaded nachos
directions: Spread each nacho with refried beans and top with cheese. Place on a cookie sheet and place in oven under broiler for 2-3 minutes until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and top with any combination of other ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: sugar-free, decaf spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 1 1/2 teaspoons per cup.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Place mixture in greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients on low
speed 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: pork and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork in skillet, then place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle rice over meat.
Add onion.

title: chicken picatta
directions: Spread cutlets out and pound to flatten.
Measure flour onto a sheet of plastic wrap and turn chicken in flour until lightly coated.
In a skillet, melt butter and oil together over medium heat.
Add 2 cutlets and cook on both sides, 3 to 4 minutes, until golden.
Remove and repeat with other cutlets.
Remove chicken and dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add to pan drippings along with lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until pan is deglazed.
Add butter and stir.
Return chicken to skillet.
Serve and garnish with lemon slices.

title: lemon chess pie(makes two pies)
directions: Prepare
pie
shells.
Leave
butter/margarine
out
to soften.
It should be very soft but not melted.
Squeeze juice from lemons and set
aside.
Separate
eggs;
refrigerate
egg whites in a bowl (not
metal).
Combine sugar and butter; beat well.
Add lemon juice, salt
and
egg yolks; beat well.
Beat egg whites until light and fluffy (not stiff); fold into sugar mixture.
Pour 1/2 of filling
into
each
pie
shell; bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce
temperature
to 350° and bake an additional 40 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: hobo beans
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms, cutting off the stems and leaving them whole.
Set aside.
Place all other ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to a boil again.
Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes or until mushrooms are tender. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Stir in corn.
Bring to boil 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk. Heat to serving temperature.

title: "light" no-bake fruitcake(162 calories; no cholesterol)
directions: Combine raisins, dates, figs, walnuts, vanilla and rum in food processor.
Blend until coarsely chopped.
Do not overblend. Spoon and press mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover with plastic wrap and place heavy object on top to weigh down. Refrigerate 2 to 3 days to blend flavors.
Unmold.
Serve thinly sliced.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Make angel food cake as directed, except use a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Cool, then slice cake longways to make 2 (13-inch) layers. Mix in large bowl until creamy the softened cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold in Cool Whip. Put some of the mixture on bottom layer. Add top cake layer. Spread remaining mixture over top cake layer. Top with cherries and refrigerate overnight.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put all ingredients, except sour cream, into crock-pot. Cook on high for 2 hours; adjust to low heat and cook for 5 or 6 hours or until tender.
hour
before
serving, add sour cream. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts until white (5 to 8 minutes).
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder in large bowl.
Boil broccoli until just unfrozen.
Layer in casserole "lasagna type" dish.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
Layer on top of broccoli, then pour sauce mix on top of broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese generously on top.
Can also sprinkle bread crumbs by Progresso or whoever on top for more seasoning.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over white rice or egg noodles.

title: onion pie
directions: Make a crust of crushed crackers and 1/2 cup melted butter. Put in 10-inch pie plate or similar low dish.
Saute until golden brown the onions in 1/4 cup butter.
Put on top of cracker crumbs in shallow casserole.
Sprinkle on top of onions grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
(This may be fixed hours ahead of time.)

title: summer chicken salad
directions: On salad plates, arrange spinach leaves, chicken, fruit, celery, almonds and green onions.
In cup, mix together mayonnaise and juice.
Drizzle over chicken mixture.
Garnish.
Makes 2 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese with sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drop frozen strawberries into gelatin and let thicken slightly in refrigerator.
Pour over topping mixture.
Chill until set.
Makes 12 to 20 servings.

title: bacon-almond dip
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
In mixing bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, chili sauce, hot pepper sauce and pepper to taste.
Add green onions, bacon and almonds and mix until blended, but still chunky.
This can be kept refrigerated for two days or frozen.
If frozen, defrost in refrigerator; if dip is too thick, add additional sour cream.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix pork, beef, rice, green pepper, onions, celery, garlic, egg, paprika, salt and pepper together.
I freeze my head of cabbage or cut out core and pour boiling water into hole and simmer until leaves wilt.
Remove leaves, one at a time, and slice off thick vein.
Place a spoonful of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf and roll up, tucking in sides. In a large pan or crock-pot, make a bed of half a can of sauerkraut and place cabbage rolls on top.
Cover with rest of sauerkraut. Cover with tomato juice.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for 2 hours; more, if in a crock-pot.
Can be frozen but be sure to cook first.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Blend mixture and pour into cooked pie shell.
May use graham cracker shell if desired; refrigerate until molded.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash chicken and drain on paper towels.
Grate the peel from the whole lemon and set aside.
Cut lemon in half and squeeze the juice over the chicken, rubbing the juice into the chicken.
Coat chicken with the flour, salt and paprika and brown slowly in the heated oil.
Arrange in casserole or baking pan.
Sprinkle grated lemon peel and brown sugar over the chicken, and then cover with the lemon slices.
Pour broth over all and place the mint (if used) over the top of the chicken.
Cover and bake in 375° oven until chicken is tender, 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove mint before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 if chicken pieces are large.

title: heavenly rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together. (A box of dry Jello may be added for color.)

title: lori's green bean supreme
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: easy cheese enchiladas
directions: In saucepan, combine and heat picante sauce and tomato sauce. Combine cheeses.
Halve 12 olives and set aside.
Chop remaining olives and mix with green onions.
In frying pan, heat small amount of oil.
Fry each tortilla on one side until lightly browned.
Dip fried tortillas into sauce; remove and fill uncooked side of tortilla with spoonful of onions, olives and 2 large spoonfuls of cheese.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Mix with apples. Put into a pastry-lined deep dish pie pan.
Pour melted butter over all.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour large tube pan. Cream butter and sugar, adding eggs one at a time.
Mix well after each addition.
Add flour and baking soda, then vanilla and sour cream, mixing well.
Stir in coconut.
Spoon into tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Do not test with toothpick too often or too soon as cake may fall.

title: canned okra
directions: Wash and cut enough okra to fill a 4-quart boiler. Cover with water, then add vinegar and salt. Cook until okra changes color. Put in hot sterilized jars and seal. When getting ready to eat, open and pour into colander. Run under cold water for 5 minutes. Let drain well. Batter and fry.

title: white butterfruit cake
directions: Cream butter, flour, mace and baking powder together.
Beat eggs and add sugar and vanilla.
Add this mixture to the butter and flour and mix well.
Add chopped fruits, nuts and raisins; mix.
Bake at 275° to 300° for about 2 hours.
Makes 10 pounds.

title: chicken with peppers and white raisins
directions: Saute chicken in butter and olive oil.
Take chicken out and saute slightly the onion and peppers.
Then put chicken back with onions and peppers.
Pour in chicken broth and bring to boil. Scatter raisins over chicken and simmer, covered, for 1/2 hour. Chicken should have skin side up.
Serve with rice.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Shape into balls.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat balls.
Bake at 450° for 35 minutes.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl with whisk.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Heat pan with oil.
Fry pancakes; flip when ready. Serve with butter and syrup or topping of choice.

title: missy's sugar cookies
directions: Blend together brown sugar, sugar, eggs, salt, vanilla and 2 sticks softened margarine.
Mix well.
Blend in 2 1/2 cups of self-rising flour.
Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yummy!

title: kid's cheese art
directions: Have kids cut cheese with cookie cutters and then paint with favorite condiment.
Put on top of cracker and enjoy!

title: creamed eggs & ham
directions: Spread toast with deviled ham and heat in slow oven until warm. Chop eggs.
Melt butter and blend in flour and salt until smooth. Add milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Stir in chopped eggs.
Cook and stir until heated through. Spoon over toast and sprinkle with paprika.

title: italian ricotta cookies
directions: Cream margarine, eggs and Ricotta.
Add sugar, flour and baking powder.
Roll dough with hands into very small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes. Do not brown cookies.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar, flour and mustard.
Stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Serve hot with warm smoked sausage links, thinly sliced.

title: rice with curry
directions: Prepare any kind of white rice you like and add just the 1/2 teaspoon of curry.
Set aside.
Add 3 tablespoons raisins; stir.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Mix jello and water; cool.
Add ginger ale, drained pineapple (reserve juice) and bananas.
Cover with marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: karo crazy crunch popcorn
directions: Mix popped corn and nuts on a cookie sheet or a large pan. Combine margarine and Karo in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat (234°) for 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns light caramel color.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over popped corn and nuts.
Mix to coat well; spread to dry. Break apart and store in tightly covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds.
I make it in popped corn balls.

title: lemon cloud pie
directions: Prepare filling mix according to directions on package.
Add cream cheese to cooked filling and beat well.
Combine whites and sugar.
Beat until forms stiff peaks.
Fold into filling.
Spoon in pie shell.
Chill this before serving.
Sprinkle crumbled pastry pieces around edge.

title: ginny's apple pie(new england)
directions: Put the bottom crust in a deep pan.
Mix flour and sugar together.
Spread 3 tablespoons of sugar/flour mixture.
Fill the plate half full of apples.
Spread half the remaining flour mixture on top of apples.
Scatter about 10 pieces of cheese about the size of your little finger.
Fill the plate heaping full of apples. Spread the rest of the flour mixture on top.
Sprinkle on cinnamon and dribble on the molasses.
Toss on 8 or 10 small chunks of butter.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 400° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon munchies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then brown tops.
In place of salmon, you may substitute 6 small cans of turkey or chicken.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat well the first four ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add the last four ingredients; beat well.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in frying pan with butter. In bowl, combine crab meat, black pepper, mustard, barbecue sauce and eggs.
Mix with sauteed mixture.
Place 1/2 in lightly greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining crab mixture with 1/2 the soup and put in casserole.
Top with remaining soup, then bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Sift and measure sugar.
Add baking powder and salt to sugar and sift again.
Soften butter or margarine.
Cream with sugar mixture until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla and beat again.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, and beat after each addition.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red hot cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Soak cucumbers 24 hours in lime and 8 1/2 quarts water.
Drain and wash the cucumbers well (be careful of cucumber rings.)
Make a solution with the alum, 1 cup vinegar and red food coloring; add with enough water to cover.

Simmer 2 hours or until tender; drain. Make syrup of red hot cinnamon candy dissolved in 2 cups hot water, 3 cups white vinegar, 15 cups sugar and 8 broken cinnamon sticks (I add 1 pint more sweetened vinegar.)
Bring to a boil and pour over cukes.
Let set overnight.
Next day drain, bring syrup to boil and pour over cucumbers.
Do this 3 nights.
Next day put cukes into jars and pour boiling syrup over the cukes and seal.

title: strawberry macaroon
directions: Combine cake mix, egg, water, shortening and 1 cup coconut; mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Whip cream and fold in strawberries.
Spread over the baked cake.
Top with remaining coconut.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mom's chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Skim off fat.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic and saute until slightly limp.
Add rest of ingredients, except beans and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Slightly drain beans and add to chili.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: holy moley guacamole salad
directions: Heat shells at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Line shells with lettuce leaves.
Combine all remaining ingredients and spoon approximately 1/2 cup guacamole into each shell.
Garnish with more lettuce if desired.
Use parts of shell for dipping.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish in 350° oven. Sprinkle with sugar, nuts, cranberries and pineapple. Add water to reserved juice to equal the amount of liquid specified on cake mix package. Prepare as package directs.
Spread over fruit. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool 5 minutes and invert onto large serving dish. Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: quick corn pudding
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Spray a 1 1/2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Chop the green onions finely. Place the butter in a small microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High until melted, about 15 to 30 seconds. Drain whole kernel corn.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugars and cinnamon in a bowl.
Separate biscuits and cut into quarters.
Coat several pieces at a time in the sugar mixture until all pieces are coated.
Put the pieces into a well greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: judy's hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon in hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes (longer if potatoes are frozen).

title: potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water and onion. Boil with salt until 1 1/2-inches of water left. Add milk, butter, salt and pepper. Serves 8.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter cups(miniature)
directions: Cream butter,
peanut
butter
and both kinds of sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Blend into
creamed
mixture
to	make dough.
Preheat oven to 375°. Shape
dough
into	1-inch balls and place in ungreased small muffin
tins.
Bake
for
to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and press
peanut
butter cup into center of each cookie until the top
of
the peanut butter cup
shows.
Remove from pans when cooled.

title: blintz bubble ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut cream cheese into 20 pieces and shape into balls.
Flatten and press each biscuit to a 3-inch diameter.
Combine sugars and cinnamon; on each biscuit place 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon and 1 ball of cream cheese; bring up edges and seal.
Pour butter into bottom of 5-cup ring mold. Sprinkle half of nuts and half of rest of sugar and cinnamon into mold.
Place half the biscuits atop, seam side up.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° until browned, about 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate.
I play a lot with this recipe. I usually use more brown sugar.

title: tamale pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine cornmeal, salt and cold water. Stir in boiling water. Cook and stir until thickened. While cornmeal is cooking, saut onion in oil. Add ground beef and brown lightly. Stir in flour, olives, tomatoes, chili powder and salt. Spread cornmeal mush evenly in bottom of greased 8 x 10 baking dish. Top with meat mixture. Arrange cheese cubes on top. Bake approximately 30 minutes.

title: mom's cherry cake
directions: Put all ingredients except pie filling in mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer on slow until mixed, then beat on high until light and fluffy.
Put half the batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Spread pie filling on top of batter. Take rest of batter and spoon on lattice fashion.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream cookie sandwich
directions: Line bottom of 9-inch pan (round) with aluminum foil.
Spread ice cream in pan.
Return to freezer until firm.
Run knife around edge of pan to loosen and remove from pan.
Wrap in foil and return to freezer.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 2 (9-inch) round pans with foil.
Mix cake mix and butter in bowl until crumbly.
Place 1/2 of mix in each pan.
Press lightly. Bake for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Place 1 cookie layer on serving plate.
Top with ice cream.
Peel off foil.
Place second cookie layer on top.
Wrap in foil and freeze for 2 hours.
To keep longer, store in airtight container.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: ham biscuit spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on both sides of bread (small dinner rolls are ideal).
Add slices of ham and cheese.
Freeze and reheat at 350°.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine
cups
flour,
yeast,
sugar, salt and soda. Combine and
heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add dry mixture.
Beat
well; stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter. Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) pans that have been greased and
sprinkled
with
corn	meal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal; cover
and	let
rise
in warm place for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: sea leg pasta
directions: Cook and drain the shells.
Add the sealegs, celery, onion, mayonnaise and catsup.
Add any or all of the following: carrots, green pepper, cucumber or green peas.
Chill and decorate with cherry tomatoes.

title: baked french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut potato in wedges. Mix all ingredients and cover potato. Place on baking sheet; cook for about 40 minutes.

title: maw's chocolate gravy
directions: In saucepan on stove top, mix all ingredients together over low to medium-low heat.
Stir continually until thickened.
Takes about 20 minutes.
Serve over big buttered biscuit.

title: pizza crust
directions: Beat all ingredients up except egg and let stand for 10 minutes.
Add egg; add more flour to your judgment.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown in spots.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook chicken (save broth).
Remove from bone.
Melt butter; mix with stuffing.
Put half of stuffing on bottom of casserole. Layer chicken on stuffing.
Mix soups and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Put other half of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sister lea's salsa
directions: Mix
well
and	refrigerate
in covered container.
May reserve drained tomato juice to use for desired consistency.

title: icing for carrot cake
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and butter. Add salt and lemon juice. Slowly add powdered sugar.
Mix until smooth. Spread on cooled cake.

title: zucchini-tomato bake(microwave.  power:  high.  time:  6 to 8 minutes)
directions: Layer half the zucchini, tomato and onion in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with half of the salt and cheese. Repeat.
Crumble bacon coarsely over top.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix
well.
Pour into a 2 quart baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Combine in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Pat into ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Flute edges, if desired.

title: mint tea
directions: Place mint leaves, tea bag, sugar and cinnamon stick in large container; add 1/2 gallon boiling water.
Let steep 1 hour, keeping container covered; strain.
Add lemon juice and enough water to make 1 gallon.
Serve hot or cold.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° until brown and firm.

title: jewish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with all ingredients, except soup and milk. Form into small balls and brown meatballs in margarine.
Place in casserole dish.
Add the soup and milk mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: raspberry coffee cake
directions: Cut cream cheese and butter or margarine into biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in milk.
Turn on lightly floured surface. Knead 8 to 10 strokes.
On waxed paper, roll dough to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Invert on a greased baking sheet.
Remove paper.
Spread preserves down center of dough.
Fold one side to middle, then other side.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: kahlua fudge
directions: In a heavy pot, melt the chocolate chips, butter and Kahlua on medium, stirring constantly, until all is melted and well blended. Add walnuts and pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate.
Cut when cold.

title: honey oatmeal bread
directions: In
large
mixer bowl put cooking oats, butter, boiling water, honey
and
salt.	Cool
to warm.	Stir in yeast.	Add eggs and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed until smooth, 1
to 2 minutes.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy
to handle.
Turn
dough
onto	lightly floured surface. Knead	until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
(Add more flour as needed until dough no longer sticks.)

title: strawberry banana french toast
directions: In blender, blend milk, egg substitute, banana, honey, cinnamon until smooth.
Dip bread slices in mixture, place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes turning slices after 10 minutes.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream.

title: microwave choc-scotch fudge
directions: Mix butterscotch morsels and 1/3 cup of sweetened condensed milk in microwave-safe bowl.
Set aside.
Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
Mix chocolate morsels, vanilla and remaining milk in microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Spread in pan.
Microwave butterscotch morsels 45 seconds on High.
Spread on chocolate mixture.
Chill.
Turn out on plate and cut into squares.

title: grandma's rich brownies
directions: Mix together the oil, sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: marinated italian garlic chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, Italian dressing, garlic powder, a little basil, oregano and parsley together; pour over chicken pieces. Place in fridge for 20 minutes, turn once.
Place in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes with sauce poured over it.
Then spray broiler pan with Pam.
Put chicken pieces on it.
Broil until browned nicely.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, chopped corned beef and green onion. Roll into a ball and then roll over shredded cheese, covering entire cheese ball.
Chill.
Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: denver biscuits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients, then add milk.
Mix and let rise for about 1 hour.
Beat batter down and add the last four ingredients.
Mix again.
Knead dough and cut into biscuits.
Freeze on a cookie sheet, then put into plastic bags.

title: tennessee special cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large bowl and mix with a spoon. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Blend in Mazola corn oil thoroughly with fork.
Sprinkle all water over mixture.
Mix well.
Press dough firmly into ball.
If too dry, add 2 tablespoons water.
Roll out between 2 pieces of waxed paper (work quickly, dough will be crumbly fast).
Put on pie plate to bake.
Makes 2 pie crusts.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers, onion and turmeric.
Dissolve salt in cold water and pour over vegetables.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours. Drain.
Cover vegetables with cold water and let stand 1 hour. Drain thoroughly.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe container.
Cook 4 minutes on High; stop.
Stir well.
Return to microwave on High for 4 more minutes; stop.
Stir in butter.
Microwave on High 2 minutes longer.
Stir in vanilla. Add baking soda; quickly stir until light and foamy.
Immediately pour out onto a lightly greased surface (baking sheet, marble slab); spread to about 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 1 pound.

title: holiday buffet chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of a baking dish with ham; position chicken breasts over.
Combine soup, half and half and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and allow to cool slightly before serving.
Sauce thickens as the dish cools.
Serve with a rice casserole or rice.
Serves 6 to 10, depending on the size of the chicken breasts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: creamy white icing
directions: Mix the 4x sugar and eggs in bowl.
Boil 4 tablespoons sugar and water.
Add boiled mixture, Spry and vanilla; beat well until creamy.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Heat oil carefully.
Sprinkle seasonings and bread crumbs over oil, stirring to distribute.
Toss chicken strips into oil and saute until cooked.
Meanwhile, prepare mostaccioli as directed on package.
Gently heat vegetables until tender (do not overcook). Toss chicken mixture, vegetable mixture or sauteed peppers and pasta together.
Serve immediately.

title: banana walnut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Thoroughly blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir in banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add nuts and mix well. Pour in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix ground beef with taco seasoning and brown.
Crunch up Doritos in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch deep pan.
Soften beans with a little milk, then spread beans over top of chips.
Spread taco seasoned meat over beans.
Cover with sour cream, then cheeses.
Bake until cheeses melt and beans are warm (about 12 to 15 minutes at 350°).
Take out of oven and sprinkle with olives. Let cool for 30 to 45 minutes, so it can be sliced without falling apart.
Shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes may be added on top.

title: all around dinner(grandma hill's recipe)
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in a long Pyrex casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup rice, salt, stewed tomatoes and Worcestershire sauce. Top each pork chop with a slice of onion and green pepper.
Add 2 cups water.
Cover with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. (You can tell if it's done by the look of the rice.)

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
While hot, add tuna (drained) and mushroom soup.
Mix together thoroughly. Put in casserole dish and top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Put in oven at 350° until crumbs are brown.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: no cholesterol rolls
directions: Set yeast and warm water aside.
Mix milk, sugar, 2 cups flour, egg and oil.
Add yeast mixture, then add other flour.
Let rise until double (approximately 45 minutes).
Work dough and knead in bowl.
Pinch off or roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: my favorite casserole
directions: Empty soups into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Add rice and mix well. Put chicken on top. Salt, and pepper; dot butter over all. Cover and bake in 275° oven for about 4 hours.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Mix other ingredients with hamburger mixture and heat. In a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole, layer mixture with Doritos, ending with mixture on top.
Heat in oven at 350° until it starts boiling.

title: sauce
directions: Add butter, water and milk to chocolate and bring to a boil. Stir in sugar and salt.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Serves 4.

title: baked potatoes supreme
directions: Thaw potatoes and put in baking dish.
Mix together soup, sour cream, margarine and cheese.
Heat until melted, then pour over top of potatoes and mix together.
Cover and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: baked sausage and eggs
directions: Cook sausage until soft, breaking into large pieces.
Drain and set aside.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, drain and press out as much liquid as you can. Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add soup mix and spinach.
Store in refrigerator.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and re-measure.
Add soda, allspice, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour batter into 3 prepared pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Ice with following recipe.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Mix well. Add nuts and apples. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fluffy lemon berry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually beat in milk until well blended. Add pudding mixes. Beat 2 minutes or until smooth. Immediately stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate 3 hours or until set. Garnish with berries.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and chill overnight.
Serve with vegetable sticks.
Also good with rye bread or sourdough bread cubes.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Crush potato chips with rolling pin before opening.
Mix crushed potato chips with garlic salt and pepper on waxed paper.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in potato chip crumbs.
Place pieces on pan, skin side up, so they do not touch.
Pour rest of butter and crumbs over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Do not turn chicken.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms.
Place frozen vegetables in strainer and thaw with hot water.
Mix rice and soup in large bowl, adding some water to reach desired consistency.
Add chicken and vegetables. Season with salt, fresh ground pepper and thyme to taste.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dry orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (do not dissolve Jell-O in water, use it dry).
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Ready to serve.

title: masked apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Fill each apple with jam or jelly.
Top with a tablespoon of cream puff dough.
The dough will cover the apple while baking on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
In a large saucepan, melt chocolate and butter.
Gradually add milk and coconut. Combine eggs and sugar; stir into chocolate mixture, mixing well. Pour into pie crust and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: low-fat flounder
directions: Thaw flounder if frozen.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Place fish in single layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour cooking sauce evenly over fish.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Fish is done when flesh is opaque and flakes easily with fork.
Garnish with lemon wedges and dill.
Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add bananas, milk, sour cream and dry ingredients.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Put hash browns in a large bowl and defrost just enough to come apart. Add 1/4 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Take the other 1/4 cup butter and mix in small bowl with corn flakes. Keep out several spoonfuls for top and put rest in other ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Put into buttered 3-quart casserole, 9 x 13-inch dish or 4 small baking dishes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May be covered with foil and stored in refrigerator for baking or in freezer for later use.

title: cheesy tuna 'n rice muffinlettes
directions: Combine rice, green pepper, cheese, tuna, olives, onion, parsley and Season-All.
Stir in eggs and milk, mixing thoroughly. Spray 6 muffin cups with Pam.
Divide rice mixture evenly among cups.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Loosen with spatula and arrange on serving plate.
Serve with Tangy Butter Sauce (below) and enjoy!!
Makes 6 servings.

title: amaretto cheese balls
directions: Beat cheese
with
Amaretto.
Form into balls and stuff with almonds, in porcupine fashion.
Chill.
Serve with crackers and fruit, such as grapes, apples and pear wedges.

title: mini brownie treats
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions for fudge-like brownies. Fill paper lined miniature muffin cups (or I just spray with vegetable spray and don't use paper) 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Immediately top each with a Hug candy. Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack to cool completely. Yields 4 dozen.

title: strawberry ice
directions: Place strawberries in blender container or food processor bowl. Cover; process until smooth.
Gradually add strawberries to Marshmallow Creme in large bowl of electric mixer, mixing until blended.
Blend in juice and peel.
Pour into 9-inch square pan. Freeze until almost firm.

title: creamettes pizza style
directions: Prepare macaroni; drain and set aside. Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add sauce and seasons. Simmer about 5 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and heat.
Serve with chips (tortilla).

title: strawberry butter
directions: Have berries and butter at room temperature.
Beat at high speed with mixer, blender or processor until berries and butter are a creamy smooth mixture.
Serve on hot biscuits.

title: trade winds salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Melt butter and brown sugar; add ham, cooking until brown.
Combine all ingredients and chill. Serves 6.

title: idiot rolls
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine, Crisco and 1 cup water; remove and cool.
In a mixing bowl, combine yeast and 1/2 cup lukewarm water; set aside.

title: vermont maple cake
directions: Separate the eggs; beat separately.
Heat 3/4 cup syrup to a boiling point.
Slowly pour in yolks, beating constantly.
Fold in beaten whites, vanilla, salt, flour and baking powder.
Bake in greased tube pan in 325° oven for 50 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; salt to taste.
Place avocados in pan. Next, put layer of sour cream, then taco sauce.
Top with olives, cheese and green onions.
Serve with chips of your choice.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Drain orange slices, pineapple tidbits and cherries.
Mix fruit with remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Mix slightly before serving. Garnish with cherry halves and a sprig of mint (optional).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill until congealed.
Real good with turkey, chicken, ham, roast or barbecue.

title: meat marinade
directions: Marinate white meat 12 hours.
Marinate red meat 24 hours.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut 1/2 meat from bone and brown in hot fat; add remaining meat and bone to cold water.
Add browned meat, onion, salt and cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook 1 hour longer. Cook on medium heat.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans or coconut.
Should make well over 100.
Cover dough while rolling the balls or it may dry out and it will be hard to get coconut to stick.

title: hot mushroom dip
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, crumble and remove from pan.
Reserve drippings; add mushrooms, onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until tender and mushroom juice has slightly evaporated mix in flour.

title: butter beans with tomato sauce and parmesan
directions: Heat beans, stock, tomato sauce and bay leaf in a large pot. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Uncover and add pepper to taste. Cook 5 minutes or longer to thicken.
Discard bay leaf and serve in bowls with grated fresh Parmesan cheese on top.
If you use canned stock, there is no need to add salt.

title: cream cheese blueberry pie
directions: Mix confectioners sugar with cream cheese until creamed.
Whip Dream Whip by directions and mix into cheese and sugar mixture. Add chopped nuts.
Pour into cooled pie shells and spread with blueberry pie filling (1/2 can each).
Chill thoroughly.
May use cherry or strawberry in place of blueberry.

title: barb's scottish shortbread
directions: Mix together by hand and knead and knead.
You cannot handle it too much, more is much better.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pat in about 1/2 to 3/4 inches thick.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with sugar while hot.

title: streusel topping
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well with pastry blender.
Toss
with fork until crumbles.
Use for apple or fruit slices or topping fruit pies or coffee cakes.

title: peg's penicillin soup
directions: All broth seasonings are optional.
Add lib!
Add veggies (stir-fry in a little olive oil first).

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: First, boil chicken until done.
When chicken is done, shred it into pieces.
Layer tortilla chips on the bottom of casserole dish.
Put shredded chicken on top of chips.
Mix cream of chicken, cream of mushroom, and rotel.
Pour mixture on top of chicken.
Cover the top with mozzarella and cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 350 degrees until cheese is melted, approximately 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain well.
Beat 3 eggs and add to the noodles. Add Parmesan cheese and mix.
Brown ground beef and add to spaghetti sauce.
Butter an oblong baking dish (do not use a metal pan) and put noodle mixture in.
Cover with meat sauce and add Mozzarella cheese and more Parmesan cheese to cover top.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns, about 30 minutes.

title: vanilla cream pudding
directions: Add sugar and salt to flour. Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add small amounts of cooked mixture to eggs. Stir egg mixture into remaining cooked mixture. Return to heat and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and oleo.
Let cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Crumble 1/2 of cake into bottom of punch bowl.
Mix one box pudding as directed and pour over cake in bowl.
Layer 1 can cherries over pudding, next 1 can pineapple (drained).
Now, cover with bananas, sliced.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat layers.
This makes a very large cake.

title: seashore bliss
directions: Place rice in a 2-quart baking dish.
Add scallops (chopped if sea scallops) and shrimp.
Combine cream, melted butter, clam juice, wine, seafood seasoning and chopped garlic.
Add to baking dish.
Sprinkle with chopped onion tops and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add milk and vanilla, then flour.
Beat well.
Makes 3 good layers.
Use any good filling.
Here are some suggestions.

title: quick chic
directions: Boil 4 chicken breasts until done, then debone.
Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over chicken.
Spread 1 can cream of mushroom soup on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top lightly and sprinkle paprika for coloring.
Cook about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no cook delights
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well.
Form into 1 inch balls and roll them in coconut.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Fry hamburg and drain grease.
Add broth, water, Lipton soup mix and celery.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and vegetables. Boil 15 minutes.
Add rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Boil 10 minutes.
Makes quite a bit.
Freeze some for later.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put all ingredients in pan; cover with 3 trays of ice.
Let set for 3 hours.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Crumble bread; add all other ingredients except margarine. Pour into crock-pot and dot with margarine.
Cook on high for 2 hours or low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: pecan-cream cheese-butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and then add flour gradually.
Fold in pecans and butterscotch chips.
Bake at 325° in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick micro fudge
directions: Place chocolate pieces, salt, flavoring and sweetened condensed milk in large glass bowl.
Place in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes (High heat setting).
Remove from microwave and quickly stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts and pour on buttered plate or a glass cake pan.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add flour, wheat germ and soda to dough and then mix in mashed bananas.
Bake for approximately 1 hour.
Makes about 8 pieces.

title: oatmeal coconut cake
directions: Boil oats for 20 minutes.
Mix together other ingredients. Add oats.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix nuts, raisins, cherries, mixed fruit and dates.
In another bowl, mix flour, sugar, eggs, butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Cook 3 hours at 250°.
Makes a large cake.
One half of this recipe makes a tube pan full.

title: mindy's chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and crumbs.
Fry until lightly browned. Remove and place in greased baking dish.
Cover each piece of chicken with a slice of Mozzarella cheese and sprinkle with paprika.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add 1 beaten egg, flour, baking powder and baking soda alternately with buttermilk; add vanilla. Drop on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp fricassee
directions: Simmer the crab boil mix, water and lemon slices for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp; bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Drain and save the liquid.
Peel.
Save lemon slices.
Make a roux in an iron skillet of the flour and oil.
Stir over medium heat until dark brown.
Add shrimp stock, onion, garlic, thyme, cayenne, black pepper, salt and sugar to the roux and cook slowly, stirring frequently, until onion is very soft.
If too thick, add a little of the remaining shrimp stock.
Stir in peeled shrimp and heat.
Mix in parsley or onion tops and heat.
Serve with steamed rice or very fresh soft white bread.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp and wash with cold water.
Mash shrimp.
Cut up onion and add to shrimp.
(Use enough mayonnaise to make moist.) Let set overnight.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in 3-quart saucepan.
Drain.
Add sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Cook lasagne according to directions.
Drain.
Rinse and lay out on foil or wax paper to keep from sticking.
Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour about 1/2 cup meat sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange 4 to 5 noodles lengthwise across sauce, overlapping edges.
Spread 1/3 of cheese mix over noodles and top with 1 cup meat sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagne, cheese and meat sauce twice.
Top with a layer of lasagne and remaining meat sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan. Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove foil and bake additional 10 minutes.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before cutting.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix together.
Can use 1/2 of sherbet in recipe if desired.

title: corned beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs and put in 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot bubbly.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Use back of floured fork to form crisscrosses.
Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: stuffed potato skins
directions: Heat the butter in a large nonstick skillet. Add the onion and a little salt and cook over medium heat until softened, about 5 minutes. Add the bell pepper and continue to cook until just tender, but still
crunchy, about 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in paprika and set aside. Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out the flesh, keeping the pieces coarse. Keep the skins warm.

title: hamburger corn casserole(a new england potluck supper favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly brown ground beef.
Add chopped onion.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add corn, soups, sour cream, pimento, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in noodles. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over the top of the casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Boil until clear and thickens, stirring often.
Add strawberry gelatin; mix and cool. When mixture has cooled, add fresh strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Let chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown round steak in oil.
Add onion and garlic.
Simmer until meat is tender.
Combine remaining ingredients; add them to the meat and heat.
Serve over noodles.

title: cannellini bean soup(white kidney beans)
directions: In medium size soup pot, add olive oil, onions and garlic over medium heat. Soften onions. Add chicken broth, bouillon cubes, tomatoes, mushrooms and carrots. Cook until carrots are half done and add drained cannellini beans. Let simmer until carrots are done and beans are hot. Goes good with a grilled ham and cheese sandwich.

title: black bottom "angel pie"
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly in a saucepan.
Beat egg yolk and milk together.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Add chocolate and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and beat with rotary beater until smooth.

Place pan in a bowl of ice water or chill in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon. Fold in whipped evaporated milk and vanilla. Turn into a baked pie shell and chill until firm. Top with whipped cream. Serves 9.

title: soft chocolate truffles fantasy
directions: In top double boiler, heat cream with butter until butter is melted.
Add chocolate chips, salt and vanilla; stir until chocolate is melted.
Remove from heat and beat in the yolks until blended.
Add sugar and Grand Marnier and beat until smooth, about 1 minute.
Line an 8 x 12-inch pan with plastic wrap extended about 4-inches over the sides.
Spread chocolate evenly in prepared pan and refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares and sprinkle top with sifted cocoa.
Remove each square and dust with cocoa on each side.
Place in bonbon wrappers and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 96 (1-inch) squares.
Delicious!

title: quick parmesan biscuits
directions: Take any refrigerator ready-to-bake biscuits and dip in milk. Roll in mixture of Parmesan cheese and a dash of garlic powder. Bake as directed.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate cauliflower into small pieces.
Wash and drain good. Sprinkle salad
mix
and bacon pieces over cauliflower. Mix together, then add enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, butter and pecan chips.
Spread evenly over bottom of pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Quarter potatoes; toss in melted butter and salt.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce and bake 15 minutes until done.

title: mai tai pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Eagle Brand and juice concentrate until smooth.
Add rum and liqueur. Fold in whipped cream; turn into crust.
Freeze or chill until firm (4 hours in freezer, 2 hours in refrigerator).
Garnish with orange slices, if desired.
Refrigerate or freeze leftovers. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: beef casserole
directions: Place rice in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Cover and bake for 2 hours at 300°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler. Mix in whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered and stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Place a layer of Nilla wafers in 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl and layer of bananas, repeating step again and ending with Nilla wafers on top.
Pour custard over Nilla Wafers and bananas. Beat 3 egg whites until stiff and add 1/2 cup sugar. Put on top of pudding and bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Combine eggs and margarine.
Add other ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into
unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: rum cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flavorings and rum.
Mix in flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all fruit, except apple in a large bowl.
Mix Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add apple to fruit.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Serve chilled.

title: fruit cup
directions: Peel cantaloupe and cut into chunks. Combine with remaining ingredients. Chill. Will keep in refrigerator 4 to 5 days. Yields about 6 servings.

title: condensed milk
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and syrup until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Pour in greased pan.
Cut in squares when cold.

title: spinach and mushroom salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine tomato puree, horseradish, poppy seed, lemon juice and salt.
Mix well by hand with wooden spoon.
Add sliced fresh mushrooms and marinate for 1 hour.
Place spinach leaves in large bowl and toss with dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: flank steak
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate flank steak overnight or all day.
Broil on both sides about 10 minutes.
For serving, cut steak on diagonal very thinly.
Use 3 steaks (about 4 pounds) for 8 adults.
Makes 1 quart marinade.
Can be saved and reused.

title: unplug drain
directions: Pour in drain.
After fizzing stops, follow with lots of boiling water.
For grease in sinks, use 1 cup salt and 1 cup baking soda, followed by boiling water.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef. Add all ingredients and simmer 1 hour or longer.
Pour over cooked spaghetti (about 1 pound uncooked). Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
In large baking dish, layer chips, beef, beans, lettuce, onion, tomatoes and cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake in 325° oven until cheese is melted and vegetables are wilted, approximately 15 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat together the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
In separate bowl combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream; blend well.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine chicken and broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Add this to chicken mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: prudent sour cream
directions: Combine the eucalyptus leaves, rose petals, rose leaves, tonka beans and orrisroot.
Sprinkle with refresher oil.
Place the mixture in a bowl or other decorative container, then arrange the cockscomb, roses and pansies on top.

title: rendang padang(spicy beef from padang, sumatra-indonesia.)
directions: Combine the seasoning ingredients, oil and water in a big bowl. Stir and mix well. Add the meat and toss to coat evenly. Allow to marinate at room temperature for 1/2 to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken in chunks.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Put over chicken.
Crumble crackers and put on top. Melt oleo and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350°.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cook chicken, let cool and shred meat.
In a large bowl, mix soup concentrates and tomatoes.

title: station 7's chili fire
directions: Cook beans for 30 to 45 minutes.
Mash up the tomatoes with a fork.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook in slow cooker 1 to 2 hours.
The longer it cooks, the better it is.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in microwave, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts. Pour onto greased pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.
Melt rest of almond bark with oil in microwave, stirring until smooth; drizzle over pizza.
Chill until firm.
Store at room temperature.

title: delicious kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Combine sugar and vinegar in boiler; bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes and cool.
Pour over kraut.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Makes 6 cups.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in large bowl. (You can shake it in a half-gallon closed container.)
Add 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to each cup of boiling water. Store leftover mix in covered container.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix well and spread on cake.

title: lemon cream cooler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add lemonade concentrate; chill until thick and syrupy.
Gently fold in whipped cream.
Pour into individual serving cups and chill until firm.
Garnish, if desired, with fresh mint leaves or fruit.
Serves 8.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: light taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Blend well. Spread on bottom of large serving tray.
Top with finely chopped lettuce, diced tomato and green pepper.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese and sliced black olives.
Just before serving, drizzle with salsa or taco sauce.
Serve with a basket of chips.

title: partlow's shrimp toast
directions: Mince all ingredients and combine with seasoning.
Trim crusts from bread and spread with mixture.
Cut bread into 4 triangles. Heat 2-inch deep oil and drop bread, shrimp-side down, into oil and brown on both sides.
Serve hot.
Yields 24.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar and milk together and put into 2-quart casserole. Then combine, brown sugar, all-purpose flour, melted butter and chopped nuts. Sprinkle ingredients over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Cut potatoes like French fries in a large baking pan. Salt and pepper. Lay pork chops over potatoes. Cut onion rings over pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: italian creme cake
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda.
Let stand a few minutes.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour and salt to cream mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into batter.
Stir in nuts and coconut. Pour into three 9-inch greased pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Debone and tear chicken.
Spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain mixed vegetables and spread over chicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into spears. Cook in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain well.
Place in shallow dish.
Combine other ingredients in a jar.
Shake vigorously.
Pour dressing over broccoli. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Sprinkle broccoli with chopped egg before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: biloxi butter
directions: Put shrimp through blender then mix with other ingredients. Serve with crackers of choice for appetizer.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix together. Shape into small cakes. Fry until golden in mixture of 1/2 butter and 1/2 oil.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan.
Stir until well blended over medium-low heat.
When thoroughly blended and heated, serve with tortilla chips.
May be reheated in microwave.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Pour peaches and juice in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over peaches.
Drizzle butter or margarine over all. Sprinkle coconut and then nuts on top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Serve with a spoonful of Cool Whip.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all at once in punch bowl when ready to serve.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in olive oil until tender.
Add black beans, sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with cooked white rice.

title: harvest turkey soup
directions: Place the turkey carcass and water in a Dutch oven or soup kettle; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Remove carcass; allow to cool. Remove turkey from bones and cut into bite-size pieces; set aside. Strain broth. Add carrots, celery, onion and bouillon; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Add the tomatoes, peas, rice, spinach, salt, if desired, pepper, marjoram, thyme and reserved turkey. Return to a boil; cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Yield: 22 servings (5 1/2 quarts).

title: chocolate frosted
directions: Combine half each of the milk, chocolate syrup, vanilla and ice cream in container of electric blender; cover.
Whirl until thick and smooth.
Pour into 3 tall glasses.
Repeat with remaining half of ingredients and 3 more glasses.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat together tomatoes, soups, broth and picante sauce.
Lay in casserole dish Doritos, chicken, onions, Velveeta cheese, heated liquid, using half of everything.
Repeat layers.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hershey pie
directions: Heat the Hershey bars until melted.
Add half of the Cool Whip and stir.
Pour mixture over crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Break 1 Hershey bar into pieces to put on top of pie.
Chill 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Fold in well-beaten eggs and beat entire mixture. Sift flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by small spoonful on greased baking sheets.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.	Put oleo, water, Crisco and cocoa
into
saucepan;
bring
to boil.
Pour over sugar, flour and mix well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Pour
into	a 16 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes
Five
minutes
before
cake	is done, make Icing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together, pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza, williamson style
directions: Put the crust in a pan.
Put on the sauce.
Put on the cheese. Put on the meat.
Put it in the oven.
Bake it for five hours. The oven is hot.

title: old fashioned drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour milk or buttermilk.
Add vanilla, using slower speed on mixer.
Mix until well blended.
Do not overbeat. Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Salt chicken and
boil until tender. Save 2 cups broth. Layer deboned chicken
in
a
1/2-inch	deep greased casserole dish.
Mix 2
cups	broth and 1 cup cream of chicken soup together.
Pour over chicken (don't stir).	Cream together flour, melted margarine and milk.	Pour over chicken. Don't stir.	Bake until brown, 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Bring all ingredients except rice to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add instant rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 8 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Arrange chicken in 12 x 8-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Microwave on High 9 to 10 minutes.
Cover with wax paper.

title: miracle whip
directions: Mix egg yolks, vinegar and lemon juice in blender.
Add pepper, salt and mustard.
Cook the sugar, flour and water until thick.
Add slowly the cooked mixture to mixture in blender. Slowly add the salad oil.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces and place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar; mix in milk and pour over cake.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice strawberries over mixture and top with glaze.

title: trail mix bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add miniature marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Add Rice Krispies cereal, granola and raisins.
Stir well.
Press into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in oil until crumbly. Add egg and orange juice.
Stir until moist.
Fold cranberries.
Spoon into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together ham, pork, crumbs, eggs, milk, salt and onion. Shape into loaf.
Place in baking pan and baste with sauce.
Cook for 60 to 90 minutes at 350° in 5 x 8-inch pan.

title: sausage roll
directions: Fry, crumble and then drain both sausages.
Sprinkle sausages and cheese over rolled out dough.
Roll up to make a ring.
Brush over the top with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mystery pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients, except brown sugar and nuts, into mixing bowl.
Combine eggs, vanilla and fruit cocktail.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apple slices and 1 cup sugar in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Mix butter, oats, flour, brown sugar and nuts. Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour until topping is browned and apples are tender.
Serve warm, plain or with ice cream.

title: beef and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on the box.
Brown meat and onion in small amount of Crisco.
Lightly grease casserole. Place a layer of macaroni in the dish.
Put meat on top of the macaroni and pour 1 1/2 cans of sauce over the meat.
Add the rest of the macaroni on top of the meat and pour the rest of the sauce on the top.
Bake, covered, in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: texas margaritas
directions: Fill blender with ice.
Add ingredients and blend on "crush" until mixture is "slushy."
Serve immediately.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Grate enough cucumber, rind and all, to measure 3/4 cup. Drain thoroughly and save juice for liquid in jello.
Add water to make 3/4 cup.
