Heat to boiling; remove and stir in jello until dissolved.
Chill until partly thickened.
Blend in mayo with wire whisk.
Fold in cottage cheese, cucumber, pecans, onion and salt. Can be 6 individual molds or in large mold or bowl.

title: chocolate "philly" fudge
directions: Soften the cream cheese and melt the chocolate.
Gradually add the powdered sugar, mixing well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Spread into an 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: best chicken cacciatore
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Remove onions.
In same skillet, brown chicken pieces (add more oil if needed) for 15 minutes.
Return cooked onions to skillet.
Combine undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano or basil, celery seed, pepper and bay leaves.
Pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in wine.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat 15 minutes more.
Serve with hot rice.

title: macaroni and cheese pizza
directions: In pan, cook macaroni; drain.
Add 2 cheese packets and 2 beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and orange rice casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 18 casserole dish/pan or spray with Pam. Line container with dried beef. Pour uncooked rice evenly on top of beef. Add salt, pepper, mushrooms, onions and orange juice. Mix well into rice. Add sour cream if desired. Place chicken evenly over top of mixture and place remaining dried beef on top of chicken. Pour 1/2 cup orange juice on top of chicken mixture. Place aluminum foil over dish. Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300° or bake for 1 1/4 hours at 375°.

title: banana medley
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 8-cup oiled mold.
Freeze for at least 3 hours or until firm.
Unmold and let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Decorate with whipped cream and well-drained cling peaches.

title: potato candy
directions: Add confectioners sugar to potatoes and vanilla to make stiff dough.
Sprinkle board with sugar and roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter and roll up like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator until it gets hard enough to slice.

title: roasted garlic butter
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

Cut off a small portion of the top of the garlic (if using the whole bulb of garlic). Place the bulb of garlic in the center of a small piece of aluminum foil (about 6x6 inches). Drizzle olive oil over garlic.
Seal the garlic in the aluminum foil and bake for about 30 minutes or until garlic is soft. Press each clove (using a garlic press) into the butter. Add the
2 teaspoons olive oil, and the parsley.
Beat with an electric mixer until well blended.
Chill.

title: basil butter
directions: Mix ingredients and chill well.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons dollop on each piece of meat and let melt slowly.
Your guests will just say ahhh!

title: pudding chaumeur
directions: Beat together sugar, butter and egg.
Blend in flour, alternating with milk; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the brown sugar, boiling water and 1 tablespoon butter; pour over cake mixture.
Cook for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: basic crepe
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or mixer; beat well.
Let batter stand for 1 hour.
Prepare on a hot griddle like pancakes. Fill with your favorite fillings.

title: all-purpose barbecue sauce(crockery cooking)
directions: Combine in crock-pot and cook on low 4 hours.
Makes 2 cups sauce.
Good on chicken/pork ribs, etc.

title: microwave caramel popcorn
directions: Double the grocery bags one inside the other.
Pour in the popcorn until it fills up 1/2 way.
Bring to a boil Karo syrup, butter, and brown sugar.
Let it boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove add 2 tsp soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn in the bag and stir around, make sure the popcorn is well covered.
(Roll bag) Put in the microwave for 45 seconds.
Do this 7 times.
After each interval of 45 seconds, shake the bag very well.
After the last time pour out popcorn onto wax paper.
separate and cool.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt the shortening.
Add brown sugar; cool slightly.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, baking powder and salt, then add nutmeats and chocolate chips. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 3 dozen.

title: skillet balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips with hands.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut in squares and serve cold or at room temperature.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine ingredients, chill for 20 minutes and serve.

title: soft breadsticks(go well with soup, italian food, you name it!)
directions: Thaw roll dough until still cold, but malleable (dough should be stiff, not gushy).
Stretch rolls to three times their length. Mix dry ingredients together.
Dip stretched roll dough in melted butter.
Roll it in the cheese mixture, patting spices on so they stick.
Place the rolls on a cookie sheet in three rows of seven per roll.
Pat them flat.
Let rise until the rolls touch each other.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: easy gingerbread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add boiling water, then add soda mixed with hot water.
Sift flour, ginger and salt.
Stir into first mixture.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes (until top springs back).

title: knox blocks
directions: Combine jello and gelatine.
Stir in hot water.
Stir well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into squares or use cookie cutters.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then 35 minutes at 350°. Total baking time is 45 minutes.
This is a very old family recipe.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and mix dry ingredients, eggs, raisins and nuts.
Add vinegar to soda; pour over dough and mix.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Soften butter; combine with sugar and cocoa, then vanilla and milk.
Sprinkle pecans or coconut on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put into baking dish.
Cover top with cheese. Bake in oven 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix and jello.
Add oil, water and eggs and mix. Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: The day before, bake cake according to directions on box in glass rectangular baking dish (13-inch).
When completely cooled, poke holes with fork and pour Kahlua on cake.
Refrigerate overnight.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.

title: jo's pomegranate jelly
directions: Combine juices and pectin. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Add sugar.
Mix well and bring to a full rolling boil, stirring for 2 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars.
Yields 3 pints.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
Marinate 5 hours before serving.

title: cream cheese dainties
directions: There's no sugar in this dough.
The cookies' sweetness comes from apricot preserves.

title: roast beef sandwich
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter or oil.
Add meat.
Cook until heated through and through.
Remove from heat and put on hoagie rolls.
Add cheese and enjoy!

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Add toast to melted margarine.
Mix together in a large bowl the pineapple, eggs, sugar and flour.
Add the toast and magarine.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes in oven.

title: sour cream cut-out cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add the sour cream.
Then mix flour mixture to the creamed mixture, a little at a time.
Stir until smooth.
Place in a covered bowl and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured surface 1/8-inch thick.
Use favorite cookie cutters.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Cut Twinkies in half. Place in bottom of pan. Spread cake icing on top of Twinkies. Sprinkle walnuts on top of icing. Cover with the can of strawberries and finally, enjoy.

title: lemon extract cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flavoring. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Have shortening at room temperature.
Grease cookie sheets. Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Beat next 7 ingredients.
Stop mixer; scrape bowl.
Add sifted flour mixture.
Beat on medium scraping bowl while beating.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet.
Press lightly with a fork which has been dipped in flour to flatten cookies and make top ridged.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: steamed pudding
directions: Steam about 1 1/2 hours.

title: pioneer beans
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Mix well, bringing to a boil.
Cover and let simmer for 2 to 3 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water, if necessary.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: whiskey bundt cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients together, then add nuts and chips by hand.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in large mixing bowl until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and eggs together thoroughly. Sift together and stir in the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt. Chill dough 20 minutes. Roll dough into balls about the size of small walnuts.
Roll in a mixture of the 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until slightly browned (about 7 minutes) in a preheated 400° oven.

title: make's it's own crust pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 10-inch greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in greased 9-inch pie dish or 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot frijole dip
directions: Combine soup and sherry.
Heat 1 1/2 minutes on High power. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 cup cheese.
Cover with paper towel and cook 4 to 5 minutes or longer until it bubbles.
Garnish top with remaining cheese and serve with potato or tortilla chips.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening with sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add alternately to creamed mixture, sifted dry ingredients and buttermilk with vanilla.
Add red food coloring. If using electric mixer, remove mixer blades and fold in vinegar and soda.
Pour batter in equal portions into 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs. (Mix buttermilk powder with water.)
Then add buttermilk and bananas.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and nuts.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish. In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until you have fine crumbs. Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves side of bowl. Turn out on floured board. Roll out into a large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle apples with cinnamon, then sprinkle apples over dough. Roll up like jellyroll. Seal edges with a little water. Slice dough into 16 slices about 1/2-inch thick. Place in pan with melted butter. Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls. This looks like too much water, but the crust will absorb it. Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Makes 8 servings. Good served warm with ice cream.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Add one cup water to
hamburger and cook.
Add the rest of the ingredients and
continue
cooking.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 1/2 cups sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Place in plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters; put in bag and shake to cover.
Drop into Bundt pan (ungreased).
Melt margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon and syrup.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and drizzle over biscuits.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes and invert onto plate.
Serve warm.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and 1 cup butter.
Blend in flour. Chill 4-6 hours.
Cream 2 tablespoons butter and brown sugar together.
Add salt, vanilla and eggs Beat well.
Press chilled dough in mini muffin tins.
Put 1/2 pecans in the shells.
Add filling, sprinkle with rest of pecans.
(Pecans can be added to filling.)
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes or until brown.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruits.
Mix together with pie filling, chill.
Add bananas just before serving.

title: tingalings
directions: Put chips in microwave deep bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix chips together.
Chop nuts and stir into chips mixture.
Add chopped chow mein noodles.
Stir in with teaspoon. Take candy mixture and drop onto wax paper.
Allow 1 hour to cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen candy pieces.

title: cream cheese clouds
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed of electric mixer.
Gradually add heavy cream; mix well.
Whip until thickened.
Using back of spoon, shape 3 1/2-inch shells.
Place on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Freeze two hours or overnight. When ready, spoon pie filling over puffs.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg whites, in large baking dish and mix thoroughly.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 300°.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: This makes a single pie shell for an 8-inch pie.
Mix and roll out.
Works every time!
(Leftover pie crust can be made into a treat of cinnamon sugar crust for the "kids.")

title: krumkake
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar gradually.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Put about 1/2 tablespoon on krumkake iron and bake until lightly browned.
Wrap around cone-shaped device immediately; remove when cooled and shaped, before the next krumkake comes off the iron.
Makes about 9 dozen.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and allow to stand 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: paul's sangria
directions: Mix well and serve over ice.

title: ting-a-lings
directions: Melt the chocolate chips over hot water.
Cool.
Gently stir in the Wheaties.
Drop with tablespoon onto waxed paper.
Chill until chocolate is set, about 2 hours.
Makes about 42 clusters.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Whip cream and fold into mixture. Freeze.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna about 12 minutes.
Stir gently and drain.
Add 1 tablespoon olive oil to prevent sticking.
Saute beef and garlic powder in the rest of oil and drain off excess grease.
Add spices, tomatoes, sauce and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
In a large deep pan, lightly oiled, place noodles, alternating with sauce, then cheeses, ending with Parmesan.
Place in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Now you're ready!

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook rice using package directions.
Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine in skillet.
Add rice, mushrooms, crab meat, shrimp, pimentos, soup and milk; mix well.
Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yield:
10 servings.

title: pistachio cake (1)
directions: Mix above ingredients together, except chocolate chips and nuts, for 3 minutes on medium speed, then 3 minutes on high speed. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: tangy cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower and onion together until done.
Drain well. Place in a microwavable bowl.
Add salt.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard and mix with cauliflower and cheese.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Press onto lightly greased 12 x 16-inch pan.
Spread egg white on top.
Take off excess.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans.
Press 1/2 of pecans into batter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while hot into squares, bars or rectangles. Yields approximately 84 to 90 rectangles per pan.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saut onion and green pepper in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef and brown; drain well. Season with chili powder, salt and catsup.
Stir in corn.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Drain crabmeat and shrimp into a strainer; rinse well using cold water.
Let stand in bowl of ice water for 20 minutes to develop flavor.
Meanwhile, line chilled salad plates with layers of lettuce leaves.
Place tomato and eggs around outside edge. Set aside.
Drain shrimp and crabmeat well, using double thickness of paper towels.
In a medium bowl, toss shrimp and crabmeat with lemon juice and minced onion.
Place mound of shrimp, crabmeat mixture in center of plate.
Sprinkle with dried parsley and Mrs. Dash.
Place in refrigerator at least 30 minutes before serving. Serve with crackers and dressing of your choice.
Ranch and Lite Thousand Island are both excellent with this salad.

title: beef and beans
directions: Cook in a frypan, beef, onion and pepper until meat is browned. Drain fat.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and shrimp paella
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven; brown chicken.
Remove and set aside. Drain fat.
Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion, tomatoes and seasonings in Dutch oven until onion is tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in rice and broth.
Heat to boil.
Add chicken.
Cover.
Bake 35 minutes.
Add shrimp and peas.
Bake another 10 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Garnish with pimento and parsley.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large pot, bring water to a boil.
Add in bouillon cubes and hash browns.
Bring to a boil again, and then lower to medium. Add remaining ingredients.
Stir often.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add 1 egg at a time, beating well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into an uncooked pie shell and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: puffy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks until light, then add sugar and spices, pumpkin, milk and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into pumpkin mixture. Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool.
Serve with molasses whipped cream.
Add molasses and grated lemon rind to heavy cream.
Beat until stiff.
Serves 6.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler; stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop onto waxed paper.

title: 30-day sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Place sliced cucumbers in gallon jug.
Cover with vinegar. Cover container.
Allow to stand at room temperature 20 days.
On day 21, pour off vinegar.
Add sugar and pickling spice.
Allow to stand at room temperature 10 more days, then ready to eat.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix together in large container.
Store airtight.
To serve put 1/3 cup mix in cup and add hot water to fill.

title: darrell's steak
directions: Add steak and all ingredients to a large plastic freezer bag and let marinate for about 3 hours.

title: jeanette's hot dip
directions: Soften cream
cheese in microwave.
Mix in next 3 ingredients. Microwave 4 minutes.
Sprinkle bacon and cracker crumbs and microwave until hot.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Combine water, vegetables, seasonings and ham.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Make a white sauce of margarine, milk and flour.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Stir into vegetables and ham mixture and heat until almost bubbly.
Makes 3 quarts.
Enjoy.

title: special k cookies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together in a large saucepan. Then mix in the cereal.
Place spoon size drops on wax paper and cool in fridge for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, onion and green pepper in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the thawed peas on top.
Mix mayonnaise and Good Seasons dressing mix together and frost top of lettuce mixture like frosting.
Before serving, sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and bacon.

title: pickled roast
directions: Save bread and butter pickle juice until you have 1 pint.
Pour over your roast and bake it until done.
Homemade pickle juice is better.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Thaw spinach just enough to make a ball.
Squeeze until most all of juice is out.
Mix spinach with Ricotta cheese.
Add nutmeg and 1 egg (well beaten).
Fold in 4 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese and 1/2 cup flour.
Add Cheddar cheese and blend well.
If mixture seems too dry, add another well beaten egg (I always do). Put mixture in pie shell (unbaked) and sprinkle remaining 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, until brown on top (45 minutes if 2 eggs are used). Enjoy!

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: impossible pie
directions: Use blender.
Whip first 6 ingredients in blender.
While blending, add flour; whip.
Add coconut.
Whip 2 minutes longer. Pour into greased 10-inch glass baking pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter, Crisco and sugar until light colored and fluffy.
Beat in molasses and eggs; set aside.
In another large bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cloves and cinnamon.
Blend thoroughly with wire whisk.
Gradually mix the flour mixture into creamed ingredients until dough is blended and smooth.
Roll dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Dip tops in granulated sugar; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Store in tightly covered container to maintain softness.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: berry and banana salad(good, light dessert)
directions: Combine berries and bananas in a salad bowl.
In a small bowl, mix the sugar and orange and lemon juices until sugar dissolves. Pour over fruit and serve.
Can substitute fruit as seasonal.

title: mrs. eunice's apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and cut apple into 8 wedges.
Place one
wedge on each triangle of crescent roll, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, roll up and place in 8 x 10 x 2 inch pyrex dish.
Mix together water, margarine and sugar, bring to boil stirring constantly. Pour over top of apple roll-ups.
Sprinkle 1 tsp. cinnamon over top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gondure rice
directions: Chop pork and sausage into small pieces; put in a large pot. Add achote oil and fry until brown.
Add onions, garlic and parsley.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes more.
Add gondure beans and olives. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Then simmer for 15 minutes.
Wash rice, drain and add to sauce mixture. Cook on low heat until rice is cooked.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 10 to 15 servings.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Salt and pepper breasts to taste.
Wrap a piece of bacon and a slice of smoked chicken around each breast.
Mix sour cream and soup; pour over breasts.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°. Uncover last 20 minutes to brown.
Serve over rice.

title: chinese soy snackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250F.
Blend soy sauce, oil, garlic juice, sugar and 2 Tbsp. of water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Set aside.
Cut 3 bagels crosswise in half in semicircle.
Lay onto cut edge and cut into 7-8 thin slices.
Brush both sides of the slices lightly and evenly with soy mixture, stirring mixture frequently.
Place slices in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove bagel chips to wire rack to cool. Cool completely.
Store chips in a sealable container.

title: cheese olive balls
directions: Grate cheese and let soften.
Mix cheese, margarine, flour, seasonings and water.
Work into a smooth dough.
Use a piece of dough about the size of a walnut and flatten with fingers.
Press dough smoothly around each olive.
Bake on a greased baking sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Freeze before baking, if desired.
Yields about 6 dozen.

title: frothy orange soda
directions: Place juice and ice cream in blender. Process until smooth. Stir in soda. Makes 2 servings.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Slice bread. Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad mix. Spread mixture on bread. Add sliced cucumbers.

title: polynesian pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops in shortening; drain excess fat. Season chops with salt and pepper. Combine pineapple and juice, green pepper and Heinz 57 sauce. Pour over chops; cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Slice apples and arrange slices in the dish. Add a few dots of margarine over them and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Sift together in a bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix the eggs with a fork and add to the flour mixture.
Put mixture over apples.
Drizzle the melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: roasted tomato and mozzarella pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse and drain. Place pasta in large bowl. Cut Roasted Fresh Tomatoes into chunks; add to pasta. Add bell pepper, Mozzarella, onion, salt and black pepper to pasta. Pour salad dressing over top; toss to combine. Garnish with fresh basil leaves, if desired. Makes 4 servings.

title: souffled baked potatoes
directions: Slice top from each potato.
Carefully scoop out potato, leaving a 1/4-inch shell.
Place potato in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon filling into potato shells, mounding on top.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.
Do not overbake; keep vegetables crunchy.
(Thaw package of frozen vegetables.)

title: a man's barbecue sauce
directions: In
a
saucepan,
bring everything to boil; reduce heat and simmer,
stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Makes 1 quart.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add dry ingredients to apple mixture.
Add oil, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Apple mixture is first 2 ingredients (apples and sugar).
This is also good made with fresh pears.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Layer chilies on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix the milk, flour, eggs and salt; pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until set. Serves 4.

title: ammonia cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff to roll out. Roll out to 1/4 inch and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned (10 minutes).

title: cold beet soup
directions: Boil beets 1/2 hour (if fresh).
Slice and cut in shoestrings. Peel and quarter cucumber.
Slice and cut onion fine.
Whip cream and milk together.
Chop up dill finely.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add water and salt and pepper to taste.
Ice cubes may be added, if preferred colder.
Serve with hot, boiled potatoes.

title: mexican rice
directions: Put oil in skillet.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender, but not brown.
Add corn, salsa and broth.
Bring to boil; stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Fluff with rice.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 sausage over margarine and 1/2 grated cheese.
Beat eggs and cream together.
Pour over mixture. Top with remaining sausage, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix potatoes and melted butter. Place in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Mix sour cream, cheese, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes. Put corn flakes on top.
Pour melted butter over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: relish stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut thin slice off top of tomatoes; scoop our with melon baller or sharp knife.
Finely chop ingredients; mix well.
Stuff tomatoes.
Chill.
May be made ahead but not frozen.

title: banana split
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick margarine; press into a crust.

title: baked beans
directions: Cover beans with water and let soak overnight.
Drain and cover with water and simmer them long and slowly.
Place a few beans in a spoon and blow on them.
If the skins burst, they are sufficiently cooked.
Drain and add ingredients.
Put in crock-pot 6 to 8 hours on high.
If in oven, bake at 250°.

title: eclair cake
directions: Beat milk and pudding 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put graham crackers in bottom of pan; cover with 1/2 pudding mixture, then put layer of graham crackers on top of that.
Then add other 1/2 of the pudding mixture, ending with graham crackers. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Frost with chocolate frosting (make your own or use a chocolate frosting from a can).
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Cook noodles 6 to 7 minutes as package says; stir flour into ground beef mixture thoroughly.
Add water, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is thickened.
Reduce heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve sauce over cooked wide noodles.
Serves 8.

title: skillet beef and macaroni
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan, blend soup and milk, reserving 1/2 cup.
Stir together remaining soup mixture, rice, mushrooms with liquid and 1/2 onion soup mix. Arrange breasts on rice mixture.
Pour reserved soup mixture over chicken and sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together, then add the eggs.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Shape into rolls and put in cool place overnight.
Slice and bake in moderate oven, 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir ingredients together thoroughly.
Put into slightly greased casserole dish and bake in 325° oven for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange cream souffle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine softened cream cheese and sugar; mix well with eggbeater.
Add cold water and orange juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into dish.
Chill until firm.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown
hamburger
and onion (drain well).
Add tomatoes, green pepper,
salt, black pepper, chili powder, beef bouillon and oregano to meat;
simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Bring salted water
to
a
boil.
Add noodles gradually.
Boil until tender (drain well).

title: chicken artichoke
directions: Dip each breast into lemon juice, then into flour.
Saute in butter.
Add artichokes and saute until chicken is nearly done. Add wine; simmer over medium heat until volume is reduced to half. Add cream, broth and seasonings.
Stir well.
Remove breasts and artichokes to heated platter.
Simmer sauce again reducing to one half.
Pour over chicken and artichokes.
Serve with pasta or rice.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pea salad
directions: Break washed lettuce into bite size pieces and layer in long dish.
Sprinkle pepper, celery, pimento and onion on top of lettuce.
Break frozen peas apart and put on top of that.
Mix sugar, sour cream and mayonnaise thoroughly.
Spread that over peas.
Sprinkle the cheeses on next, then top that with bacon bits.

title: virgin mary
directions: Mix in large glass and garnish with lemon slice.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch cake pan, mix ingredients and bake according to cake mix directions.

title: leslie's salad
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with mayonnaise.
Beat in pineapple juice and add marshmallows and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and grapes.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6.

title: danish jam cookies
directions: In a large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat together butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat in corn syrup and egg yolks until well mixed.
Stir in flour until blended.
Cover; chill 1 hour or until easy to handle.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
With thumb, make indentation in center of each cookie.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on rack.
While warm, fill with small amount of jam.
May be necessary to press again with thumb before filling.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except fruit cocktail).
Put fruit cocktail in batter last.
Pour
in greased pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup light brown sugar
over
batter
and sprinkle with chopped (not ground) pecans.
Bake at
for
40 minutes.
Makes 2 cakes, 1 square Pyrex pan and one small oblong.

title: fran's flank steak(very easy recipe)
directions: Sprinkle flank steak with garlic.
Pierce steak with fork. Marinate for 3 to 4 hours.
Put under broiler with door open (very important) for 8 to 10 minutes on each side and basting with marinade sauce every 3 to 4 minutes.
Slice on diagonal (very important).
This is a melt in your mouth entree.
We love this and it is inexpensive.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips. Beat eggs and lemon juice. Marinate chicken at least 2 hours in egg mixture.
Season flour with salt and pepper. Remove strips from egg mixture and place in buttermilk. Remove from buttermilk, flour, and deep fry.

title: minted snow peas
directions: Cook peas and drain; add butter. Combine mint, vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil for 5 minutes. Pour mixture over peas. Stir to coat. Serve.

title: genny's potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel and medium shred them (4 sided grater).
Stir in sour cream and 1 cup shredded cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese; sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: summer tortillas
directions: Cut watermelon, apples and strawberries in small pieces. Combine fruit and almonds in a bowl to make a fruit salad.
Spread yogurt on tortilla shell.
Add some fruit salad and roll up shell.

title: veg beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix in vegetables, macaroni, garlic salt and mushrooms.
Put in baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add broccoli.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and milk.
Stir until smooth. Place rice in 8-inch square baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: easy microwave caramel corn
directions: Cut top off brown paper bag (top 3 or 4 inches).
I pop the corn right into the bag.
In a 4 cup measuring cup (plastic is best) with handle, melt the sugars, butter and syrup on Low in microwave.
Stir well, then cook on High 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in the soda until mixture foams some and lightens in color.
Stir syrup into popcorn in bag and mix well with a long wooden spoon. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir well and then microwave on High for 1 minute.
Cool on wax paper.

title: salad
directions: Put everything but lettuce and cheese in bowl and pour dressing over.
Let stand 1 hour.
Mix with lettuce, sprinkle cheese on top and serve immediately.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls in 11 x 17-inch pan.
Press together to seal. Bake for 7 to 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Blend Miracle Whip, sour cream, cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine vegetables and press into dressing.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium bowl.
Cut in shortening, using a pastry blender.
Add buttermilk and blend well.
Turn dough out on a floured surface and knead.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° until light brown.
Cool and freeze.
Take out and bake until brown as needed.

title: grandmother's coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over double boiler until thickened. Add margarine, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: goodnews class salad
directions: Mix greens, onions, celery and oranges together in large bowl.
In small skillet mix sugar and water. Heat to dissolve sugar;
stir in almonds to coat.
Toss almonds into salad and serve with red vinaigrette.

title: christmas morning breakfast casserole
directions: Line a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish with bread.
Crumble sausage over bread, add cheese on top of sausage.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings together; pour over ingredients in dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, covered the first 15 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: santa fe soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, cook ground chuck and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain. Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 2 hours. Top individual servings with grated cheese, sour cream and chopped green onions. Serve with tortillas or cornbread.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Empty sauce into saucepan the catsup, mustard, vinegar, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, water, 1/4 teaspoon black pepper and paprika. Cover over low heat. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.

title: dutch babies(german pancakes)
directions: Heat oven to 425°.

title: cajun chicken bites
directions: Flour chicken pieces and deep fry in hot oil. Remove from oil and drain on paper towels. While chicken is still hot sprinkle with Cajun seasoning. Serve with carrot and celery sticks and ranch dressing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Add oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Add zucchini and mix.
Stir together salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and flour.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 well greased 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard, bring to boil.
Stir in wieners and let simmer.
Keep adding wieners as long as sauce lasts.
Great fix in crock-pot.

title: main dish - macaroni
directions: Follow directions for macaroni and cheese.
When complete, add in salsa.
Mix well and serve.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Melt the butter real slow.
Add sugar, milk, egg and vanilla. Beat together.
When it comes to a boil, remove from heat.
Add a cup of crushed crackers and pecans.
Set aside.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, sugar and flour.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with butter and crumbs that have been mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare 1 quart chopped strawberries with 1 cup sugar.
Let the sugar dissolve before putting between layers.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients and add to egg mixture by hand.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 13 x 15-inch jelly roll pan (can use same size cookie sheet).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread peanut butter on hot cake right from oven.
Let cool completely and then cover with melted chocolate.

title: warren's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 30 minutes. Makes enough sauce for 4 pounds of ribs.
